text:
hot news
bermaksud membela diri terkait gerakan me too, rani mukerji malah diserang netizen di twitter 😯

rani mukherjee, tabu, deepika padukone, anushka sharma, taapsee pannu dan alia bhatt adalah aktris terbaik tahun 2018 dengan katakter film yang mereka tampilkan. mereka dikumpulkan jadi satu di meja bundar aktris terbaik 2018 dan ditanya untuk berdiskusi masalah apapun yang terjadi di industri bollywood selama tahun 2018.

disaat meluncur sebuah pertanyaan dari panitia perihal gerakan #metoo , rani mukerji yang tidak setuju dengan pendapat yang dilontarkan deepika padukone dan anushka sharma membuat netizen membanting serangan kepada rani di twitter karena komentar 'membela diri'. #metoo adalah sebuah gerakan dimana terkait dengan isu pelecehan seksual yang dilakukan oleh tokoh-tokoh industri. semua korban dan pelaku bersaing mengujar kejujuran atas kebungkaman yang selama ini mereka sembunyikan. beberapa korban dan pelaku pelecehan seksual satu demi satu terungkap dengan adanya gerakan ini.

rani mukerji adalah sosok aktris yang memiliki kepribadian yang masih sangat dicintai berkat pesona yang dibawanya dari tahun 90an dan masih berhasil memenangkan hati di layar sinema sampai saat ini, tetapi aktris 40 tahun ini pasti memiliki sudut pandang berbeda pada gerakan #metoo yang berlangsung sepanjang tahun 2018 ini, yang tidak dihargai oleh kebanyakan orang.

anushka, deepika, rani, alia, tabu dan taapsee dipanggil pada pertemuan konferensi meja bundar, dimana ia mendapatkan topik yang menjadi salah satu sorotan terbesar tahun 2018, dan berkaitan dengan selebriti wanita. anushka, deepika dan alia telah mendukung gerakan itu sebelumnya dan mereka menyatakan bahwa gerakan #metoo adalah langkah yang baik, karena sekarang orang akan berpikir dua kali sebelum bertindak di sekitar wanita.

namun, rani yang datang ke konferensi atas predikat salah satu aktris terbaik tahun 2018 dalam perannya di film hichki sebagai guru yang berdiri tegak untuk murid-muridnya yang gaduh, membuat poin yang tampak sangat aneh bagi kebanyakan ora..(selengkapnya baca difacebook) 😉

#dnaindia
#metoo
#ranimukerji
@taapsee 
@deepikapadukone 
@anushkasharma 
@tabutiful 
#aliabhatt

text:
the year of women. 
2018 marked another historic uprising of female voices, another high-point of the women's revolution that is taking place across the world. 2018 was the year of women. 
2018 was remarkable year for our movement as we celebrated the 10th anniversary of #femen. the first decade of our history ends with pride for numerous fights against male domination, with sisterhood among the activists in 4 corners of the planet and with dreams and aspirations for the future. from ukraine to france and to the rest of the world. from kiev students, to women of different age and backgrounds in france, germany, spain, sweden, netherlands, belgium, mexico, brazil, turkey, canada, usa, venezuela and czech republic. that's the journey femen made so far and we are ready to expand further. 
in 2018, femen continued to give a sextremist lesson to the patriarchs in power like turkish president recep #erdogan and the us president donald #trump. driving across the champs-elysees in paris, trump's motorcade was stoped twice by our angry political bodies. that's our female revenge. that's how we grab back patriarchy by the balls! 
in 2018 femen also contributed to the worldwide female uprising #metoo. our activists chased the celebrity perpetrators and made sure they learn that female bodies aren't always sexual objects at their disposal. we made them hear angry loud female voices. following our actions against woody allen and roman polanski, in 2018 we've faced again silvio berlusconi and finally caught bill cosby as he was about to be sentenced for numerous crimes. 
in 2018 we've denounced homophobia of conservative groups who deny the rights of gay couples for medically assisted procreation in france as well as the hate crimes against lgbt+ community in putin's russia, in tunisia and egypt. we've defended our abortion rights with protests in germany and spain and raised up against xenophobia and sexism of the far right groups across europe. 
in 2018 we stood with heroes of freedom of speech and consciences like asia bibi in pakistan and oleg sentsov in russia. femen also supported the imprisoned in france artist pyotr pavlensky. 
the world was shaken⬇

text:
new years is here! it’s a time for new beginnings... so i have a confession to make to each of you. 
initially, i told you that i started my blog to update friends & fam on my whereaboots over my 6-month backpacking trip. but, that wasn’t the truth.

the true reason i created my blog was.... to take off my mask! i was hiding who i am because i felt ashamed of the things i do in my life. not because they are immoral (far from it!), but because they’re totally unconventional; they’re beyond the conventions imposed on me by my childhood community; they’re outside the cultural norms of the corporate world i work in. 
i had fears of what people would think of me if they knew... they’d think i’m crazy; they’d assume i’m some sort of gypsy! i was suffering from constantly hiding in fear and shame... yet, i was the only one bestowing this shame onto myself, so only i have the power to remove my veil of shame!
i mean, shit, why should i feel ashamed of the things i’ve done when i find them to be so absolutely incredible?!
from enjoying the life of bucket showers & no toilet paper in remote villages, to reciting a gratitude prayer before each meal. 
from my passion for budget vagabonding travel, to my passion for self-development through meditation, free-form dance, & quitting alcohol. ...i love the unconventional me that i am, the full spectrum ❤️🤲 #booty

so, i started my blog to show my true-self & let it all be known, so i don’t need to wear a mask in public anymore 😌 #authenticity 
if you fancy checking out my blog, link in bio 😃 wanderingaboot.wordpress.com 
#wanderingaboot

#feelingfreedom, time to fly 🦅 
i’m right there with any of you who are also hiding your unconventional selves. anyone else have similar feelings? #metoo

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

in a superdeeduper eww of a session with b-town's biggest talents all on one table, ms. mukherjee, erstwhile on the list of artists i felt had integrity on screen and off, managed to do one of the best displays of foot-in-mouth i have seen. 
the topic up for discussion was  #metoo and the instance of harassment.
'i think you have to have the courage to be able to protect yourself' she says, to which deepika says not everyone is built with that dna and may feel cornered. 
rani of cringe: 'that's why we need to talk to these women and tell them they need to change.'
so. ms. mukherjee would rather the onus be shifted to the victims. classic internalised misogyny at its absolute finest. 
someone offers a contradicting opinion. actually, everyone on the table does. but nope. 
in life we need to take responsibility of our own selves, she opines. 
keeps on insisting that krav maga and martial arts classes be made compulsory in schools, in response to everyone and their mom telling her that the root issue needs to be countered. 
her victim-blaming rhetoric comes from an obnoxiously privileged place. physical strength, class protection, not having to be in public on your own, not having to take public transportation every single day. 
all of this is privilege. the thing that's causing her to verbal vomit this utter load of crap.
this is the least endearing a human can be to me. 
rani, sweetie, you're a cringefest and a trainwreck rolled into one.

text:
i believe 2018 was the year of the woman. and my year end books are so. 📖

______________________________________________

lektury końca roku. kobieta w roli głównej. bo rok 2018 wydaje mi się czasem kobiet, może nawet przełomem. jesienią ubiegłego roku #metoo zapoczątkował coś ważnego, dyskusję dużo szerszą niż kwestia molestowania seksualnego kobiet. o sprawach kobiet w ogóle. sprzyjało stulecie wywalczenia praw wyborczych przez polki (i wiele europejek). dużo ważnych w tym trendzie, choć skrajnie różnych książek: brakująca połowa dziejów, aleja włókniarek, służące do wszystkiego, czy odważne spojrzenie na cielesność kobiet u machado. niewyobrażalnie ważna dla młodych #sexed.pl anji rubik wobec wywołujących grozę, powielanych stereotypów w dobrozmianowych programach i podręcznikach szkolnych (pierwszy prezent gwiazdkowy, który doczekał się przeczytania jeszcze tego samego wieczoru). intensywnie również filmowo: o bezsensownym poświęceniu żon, czyli świetnie zekranizowana wolitzer, czy poruszające 53 wojny. fantastyczna, poszukująca swojej własnej drogi lady bird. wreszcie genialna frances mcdormand w trzech billboardach za ebbing, która jest dla mnie chodzącym manifestem siły i determinacji kobiet.

______________________________________________

u mnie na stosie z nowości tylko histeryczki (genialne). kontrowersyjny steinar bragi wywołuje nie mniej wściekłości, niż ciekawości. aktualnie powoli sączę niespieszną, dwutorową narrację maggie o’farrell. przede mną intrygująca kołysanka. zakończę kobietą sportretowaną przez hiszpańskie autorki. 
______________________________________________

to był ważny, ciekawy i inspirujący rok. mam nadzieję, że #womenpower nie okaże się chwilowym trendem. i że nie będzie używany do tagowania zdjęć z roznegliżowanymi ciałami. to mówiłam ja, kobieta ze świata bankowości inwestycyjnej, niezmiennie zdominowanego przez mężczyzn 😉 i marząca o najlepszej przyszłości dla swoich córek.✌️ #yearofthewoman#womenpower#steinarbragi#maggieofarrell#leilaslimani#roxanegay#bookevening#bookstagram#bookish#booklover #bookworm#bookaddict#bookphotography #igbooks#bookcommunity#bookcollection#igreads#bibliophile#czytam#czytambolubie

text:
2018 lider mot sitt slut. jag kommer minnas detta år som det då jag verkligen kämpat för min sak, mina mål & ambition. året då jag lärt mig otroligt mycket om mig själv & hur lite den psykisk ohälsan eller stroken överhuvudtaget definierar mig som person.
jag uppfyllde nästan alla mina löften men här är årets guldklimpar: ◽◽◽◽◽◽◽
🌹 vid världens ände fick ett rusch som jag är oerhört tacksam för. att så många känt igen sig / lärt sig nya kunskaper / fått en annan bild av psykisk ohälsa är för mig ett bevis nog på att detta ämne behöver pratas mer om. ◽◽◽◽◽◽◽◽◽
🌹 skrev klart utkast 1 + 2 (+ fler) av rena händer.
🌹 jag har fortsatt kämpa för att bryta isolering & depression genom att ta mig till gymmet även de dagar då jag inte velat eller orkat. men utan att förvärra ätstörningen, (genom att värna om bra mat och jämna vilodagar.
🌹 läst ofantligt mycket böcker!
🌹 känt mig starkare än nånsin genom att fortsätta tro på mig själv. ◽◽◽◽◽◽
🌹 firat 5 år tillsammans med den mest fantastiska människa jag nånsin träffat. ❤️ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽
name: JESSICA THÅSTRÖM
tweet_full:
2018 lider mot sitt slut. jag kommer minnas detta år som det då jag verkligen kämpat för min sak, mina mål & ambition. året då jag lärt mig otroligt mycket om mig själv & hur lite den psykisk ohälsan eller stroken överhuvudtaget definierar mig som person.
jag uppfyllde nästan alla mina löften men här är årets guldklimpar: ◽◽◽◽◽◽◽
🌹 vid världens ände fick ett rusch som jag är oerhört tacksam för. att så många känt igen sig / lärt sig nya kunskaper / fått en an bild av psykisk ohälsa är för mig ett bevis nog på att detta ämne behöver pratas mer om. ◽◽◽◽◽◽◽◽◽
🌹 skrev klart utkast 1 + 2 (+ fler) av rena händer.
🌹 jag har fortsatt kämpa för att bryta isolering & depression genom att ta mig till gymmet även de dagar då jag inte velat eller orkat. men utan att förvärra ätstörningen, (genom att värna om bra mat och jämna vilodagar.
🌹 läst ofantligt mycket böcker!
🌹 känt mig starkare än nånsin genom att fortsätta tro på mig själv. ◽◽◽◽◽◽
🌹 firat 5 år tillsammans med den mest fantastiska människa jag nånsin träffat. ❤️ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽ ◽

text_retweet:
i
#repost @hufilm1971 with @get_repost
・・・
the students of howard university film and television program call for the establishment of a department of cinematic arts and television, effective fall 2019. howard has the most comprehensive film program, and offers the only mfa in film, of any hbcu in the united states. howard university has the only minority owned pbs affiliate in the nation. for decades since the founding of the film program in 1971, we have been fulfilling a national and global need for women storytellers and storytellers of color. still, there is no hbcu in the united states with a department dedicated to the study of cinematic arts and television - we can change this.

we are calling for the first department of cinematic arts and television, at any hbcu in the nation, to include the following components:

a) independently administered budget. 
b) independently managed equipment center and facilities. 
c) shared governance by the students and faculty over said budget, equipment center, curriculum development and implementation of the undergraduate and graduate bfa and mfa programs, as well as program and instructor evaluation. 
d) and a commitment to attract more of the most qualified professors in the industry, and to continue to produce graduates of the finest caliber.

support us by signing the petition, share the campaign with everyone you know, and let howard university president wayne a. i. frederick know that the time is now for a howard university department of cinematic arts and television.

why is this important?

since 1971, the howard university film program has produced and/or supported the most highly trained and widely acclaimed storytellers, including: bradford young, hans charles, ernest dickerson, arthur jafa, jenn nkiru, malik sayeed, alan ferguson, sehkar kammula, faraday okoro, lodi matsetela, lekgetho makola, nijla mumin, maori karmael holmes, floyd rance, yao ramesar, and shirikiana aina.

with the likes of stanley nelson, michelle parkerson, julie dash, and haile gerima having served as faculty in the program.

in the new era of #oscarssowhite, #timesup, and #metoo the film and television industry is clearing space to...

text:
game day 🎉 
cette photo m'inspire amour, force et sororité 🔥 
à l'approche de 2019, je nous souhaite à toutes et à tous, une nouvelle année en amour, en force et en solidarité ❤️j'ai l'impression que les réseaux sociaux, aidés de leurs très chers hashtags, en 2017 et en 2018 ont contribué à disperser des écrans de fumée, à démasquer de grands méchants loups; qu'en dépit de leurs défauts et de leurs sombres dessous, ils ont contribué à répandre une parole engagée et engageante faite par et pour les femmes. 
je crois, même si peut-être un peu naïvement, que ces deux années ont sensibilisé des générations de filles et de femmes aux enjeux féministes, et surtout, à la pertinence de ces questions au quotidien. 
après #metoo #moiaussi #himthough #believewomen #etmaintenant j'ai hâte de voir ce que nous ferons de 2019. malgré la tristesse et la colère que certaines nouvelles et défaites provoquent- et malgré tout le travail qu'il reste à faire-, je suis fière de nous toutes. de nous, ensemble. puissantes, ensemble. et je nous souhaite une 2019 dans cette action. une 2019 qui œuvre à dégager le futur en continuant d'exposer les inégalités du présent pour faire advenir les choses autrement. 
#girls #grlpwr #2019

text:
there are days when i struggle more than others. days when things that i've tried to bury so deep within myself surface. days that i feel like i just can't do the hard things. those are the times i reach for sara. it may help individuals release and begin recovery from tramatic memory of sexual or ritual torment or other forms of  physical or emotional abuse. for me it's a necessary tool. it help me with emotional release, emotional healing and relaxation. 
i don't typically share about this part of my past because there is alot of shame for victims, alot of judgement but also so many of us that have been there. if my saying #metoo helps just one person then my putting these words out there is worth it. if you are struggling with any of these things and need a shoulder i will gladly be here for you. i don't care if i haven't talked to you in forever or if i've never met you, i am here. 
be well friends

text:
ultima publicación del 2018, con un mensaje esperanzador de simone de beauvoir.
gracias por seguirnos.
este fragmento del libro nos lleva a reflexionar  sobre sexualidad,  juventud, salud. el hombre y la construcción de mujer como  ideal de la belleza variable.  la carga de significados que se otrorgan al cuerpo femenino para que represente las cualidades inertes y pasivas de un objeto. simone habla de como se construye el concepto de cuerpo en su imanencia.

hace además un recorrido alrededor de costumbres y modas que separan al cuerpo femenino de su trascendencia. lo que conlleva que sea para el hombre “una  cosa”. siendo el papel más habitual de la mujer terminar la metamorfosis en ídolo carnal. explica la relación del hombre con la mujer en un ciclo que va de la madre a la  amante, a la  muerte.
.
.
.
.

text:
in matthew 11:28, jesus says “come to me.” he says come to me. he does not say come to my church or go to a church on sunday. he does not say come to a priest, pastor or church leader. he does not say come to a teaching or a building or a group. he says come to me, and learn from me. i will give you rest. no one else can give us the rest. we cannot earn the rest. the rest is a gift he gives us. today, we get too busy going to church and church activities that we go no more to jesus. today's church leader has convinced us that going to their church is more important than going to jesus.

text:
and so the story goes they wore the clothes
they said the things to make it seem improbable
whale of a lie like they hope it was
and the good men tomorrow had their feet in the wallow
and their heads of brawn were nicer shorn
and how they bought their positions with saccharin and trust
and the world was asleep to our latent fuss
sighings swirl through the streets like the crust of the sun, the bewlay brothers
in our wings that bark
flashing teeth of brass
standing tall in the dark
oh, and we were gone
hanging out with your dwarf men
we were so turned on
by your lack of conclusions

i was stone and he was wax so he could scream and still relax
unbelievable
and we frightened the small children away
and our talk was old and dust would flow
through our veins and though it was midnight back at the kitchen door
like the grim face on the cathedral floor
the solid book we wrote cannot be found today
and it was stalking time for the moon boys, the bewlay brothers
with our backs on the arch
and if the devil may be here
but he can't sing about that
oh, and we were gone
real cool traders
we were so turned on
you thought we were fakers

and now the dress is hung, the ticket pawned
the factor max that proved the fact is melted down
woven on the edging of my pillow
and my brother lays upon the rocks
he could be dead, he could be not, he could be you
he's chameleon, comedian, corinthian and caricature

text:
name a way you like to empower yourself. ⠀
--⠀
“there’s an amazing ted talk by amy cuddy about power poses. she talks about literally posing in ways that make you feel stronger- expansive body postures like the wonder woman pose. in other words, take up space! it’s something i’m still trying to get used to, but i’ve been trying it for a month now and i like it so far. you weren’t born to be a supporting role in someone else’s story."⠀
⠀

text:
cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

prior to the company’s role on trump’s election campaign, wylie had been its director of research. recalling his first meeting with bannon, he explained how fashion was one of the many things they examined, along with “judith butler, foucault and nature of our fractured self”. he said the pair discussed the difference between crocs and chanel’s little black dress as analogous for the fashion spectrum – which would become a blueprint for how the firm used fashion preferences later on.

wylie went onto to criticise the fashion industry for creating a “pre-existing cultural foundation which allowed the alt-right to grow over that time period”. he conceded that while cambridge analytica “exploited the cultural narratives that the fashion and culture industry put out”, the fashion industry was responsible for creating those cultural narratives in the first place. he added: “we need new narratives in culture, and to do a better job of showing more diversity” in order to direct politics along a different route.

according to the data obtained (the majority of which came from us users), certain fans of american denim brands such as wrangler, hollister and lee jeans could be more closely linked to low levels of openness and mistrust – and therefore more likely to engage with pro-trump messaging.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

prior to the company’s role on trump’s election campaign, wylie had been its director of research. recalling his first meeting with bannon, he explained how fashion was one of the many things they examined, along with “judith butler, foucault and nature of our fractured self”. he said the pair discussed the difference between crocs and chanel’s little black dress as analogous for the fashion spectrum – which would become a blueprint for how the firm used fashion preferences later on.

text:
i’m going to look back on 2018 & think “what in the actual fxxx was that.” my life is an oxymoron. this term was brought up recently in a conversation, for a situation completely unrelated to me and my life. but it resonates with me. 
i support the #metoo movement. i also support the 2nd amendment. 🔫 #2a

i have an avid love for animals, but i hunt to support conservation efforts. 🦌 #fuckpeta

i think our justice system is flawed, but i support our brave men and women who leave their families to protect me and mine. 🇺🇸 #backtheblue #thankaveteran

it takes years of self realization to be confident in what you stand for and behind. never be ashamed. even if everyone is against your beliefs. keep slaying. 
#selflove #2a #fxcktheeconomy #metoo #oxymoron

thank you so much, @kanikasasan9 for always standing in my corner. thank you @pinkorchidstudio for making me feel so incredibly beautiful. @wellgroomedinc, thank you for the masterpiece. and @sydneytangye, thank you for the space and so much more. 
believing in one another is what propels us forward as a whole society, a healthy and progressive ecosystem. i truly look forward to what 2019 shall bring for all of us. just remember, you have to put the work in. into yourself, your career, relationships, and the journey. 🙏🏼🖤 (outfit: @wellgroomedinc • makeup/hair: @pinkorchidstudio • styling: @kanikasasan9 • jewellery: @adorebykanika) // #iamresilience #hypebeaststyle #curiocityvan #dailyhivestyle #wellgroomedinc #womeninspiringwomen #womenwhorunwiththewolves #wildwomen #unwomen #womenintheword #canoncanada #dailyhivevancouver

text:
on this week’s very special episode of friends and girls, jill and cameron discuss an album that has recently gone from being an early-‘00s emo staple to a creepy casualty of the #metoo movement: brand new’s 2000 debut lp, your favorite weapon. yes, jesse lacey had been fully cancelled at this point, and our goal with this episode isn’t to redeem brand new in any way, but to honestly and truthfully explore why misogyny and toxic masculinity is so rampant in every genre of punk, and what we can do to change it.
.
.
.
.
.
#poppunk #metoo #sexism #feminism #berlin #emo #brandnew #yourfavoriteweapon #misogyny

text:
on this week’s very special episode of friends and girls, jill and cameron discuss an album that has recently gone from being an early-‘00s emo staple to a creepy casualty of the #metoo movement: brand new’s 2000 debut lp, your favorite weapon. yes, jesse lacey had been fully cancelled at this point, and our goal with this episode isn’t to redeem brand new in any way, but to honestly and truthfully explore why misogyny and toxic masculinity is so rampant in every genre of punk, and what we can do to change it.
.
.
.
.
.

petite précision avant que vous lisiez le texte ça représente ce que j'ai ressentit en instantané pas ce que je pense à l'heure actuelle ! je ne cherche pas à ce qu'on me plaignent ou autre, je vais très bien xd je veux seulement sensibilisé les gens à cette cause. 
après l'orage,
j'ai perdu mon corps,
il est souillé,
j'ai mal, horriblement mal, 
c'est terriblement douloureux,
mentalement comme physiquement

cette violence m'a détruite,
réduite à néant..
j'ai était une vulgaire serpillière,
une vulgaire fille de plus,
on m'a souillé.

on a souillé mon corps,
je n'en veux plus,
ce n'est plus le mien,
je refuse de savoir que par cet voie d'autres hommes sont sensés repasser,
par cette voie qui est meurtrie et par laquelle on m'a anéantie.. je ne veux plus...je ne veux plus..jamais.

.

“i run for no reason at all. i run because it brings me to life” .
*************************************
.
.
... 2016: was dedicated to reduce weight & learn basic running techniques.
.
.

.
.
... 2018: dedicated to endurance & technical running, & understanding my body functionality.
.
.
... 2019: 😬😁? .
*************************************
.
... thank you 2018, you’ve been remarkably awesome🙏🏽♥️
.
.  2018 highlights:
.
.
✅ finished my first ultra 50k trail race.
✅ finished my first official 30k trail race.
✅ did my first relay race. ✅ did my first devil plunge run training.
✅ did my first mother hump run training.
✅ did my first run training to “the mosque”. ✅ broke my fossil rock climb record.
✅ broke my 5k record in 27:35min. ✅ did my first run training in yibir, janis, & hafeet mountains. ✅ attended my dream singer concert julio iglesias. ************************************* .
2019 goals?
.
.
* more running training.
* finish all uu trail & desert races. *
* more of life minimalism.
* book writing!
* empowering more females. .
*************************************
.
.
my tons of thanking goes to 🙏🏽:
.
.
* my coach, the one & only, mr. lee harris.
* myself, omaima.
* my kids, lady zeina & lady zayan.
* my dtr friends.
.
.

text:
ett av mina absoluta favorit budskap som får summera det gångna året än en gång! skrev delar av denna text även förra året och stämmer så bra än så delar igen.. är inte ngn som direkt lever efter nyårslöften när det kommer till "nystart" osv utan önskar mer att leva här och nu..
men känner att det är fint att ta sig tid att reflektera över tid som varit tex det gångna året och känna efter om det är något jag önskar fokusera mer på. och kring nyår kan ju var en sådan tid.🔹något som har berört mig även detta år.. in på djupet och som gör mig sådär jävla urgrunds ledsen men samtidigt hoppfull är allt som kommit upp och blivit synbart med #metoo . ledsen för att det är så hemskt att det har varit och är på detta sätt. hoppfull för att nu kan vi tillsammans göra detta synligt och tillsammans jobba mot att det inte ska behöva vara såhär, tillsammans för jämlikhet..ett steg i taget.. tillsammans mot förändring!! jag kommer aldrig sluta att prata om/skriva om/uppmärksamma detta! det för mig som kvinna, för mina döttrar,  för min mamma, för mina medsystrar..🔹på ett proffesionellt plan har jag haft ett givande och utvecklande år, jag älskar mitt jobb och ser fram emot att få fortsätta att utvecklas/lära mig mer och även kunna få hjälpa/vägleda fler kvinnor med tänket att bli stark inifrån och ut. känner mig väldigt privilegierad att få jobba med det jag brinner för!! 🔹på det privata planet så har detta år varit både upp och ner precis som livet är. och då blir det tydligt vad som för mig är extra viktigt.. bla att det spelar ingen roll "vad andra gör" eller "hur andra gör", det finns verkligen inte bara ett sätt att göra saker på oavsett vad det gäller, personligt eller proffesionellt. 
att våga stanna upp, be om hjälp och ha ett mer "tillsammans" tänk. 
ibland behöver man "känna" sådär på riktigt på det som gör ont, det som får ens andetag att värka i bröstet och låta tårarna bli till en riktig "fulgråt" för att kunna resa sig och ta nya tag.. så är det ngt som jag tar med mig lite extra mkt in i det kommande året är det den oändliga kärleken jag känner för min familj och mina nära vänner/medsystrar som funnits/finns vid min sida ❤️ oändligt tacksam ❤️ gott nytt år ✨
name: Anna R Landaeus

text:
sunday night vibe! 
borrowed from @the_female_lead .
what have you stood up for this year? .
at future female we have stood up for everyday equality, by raising awareness of everyday habitual sexism. often it’s conscious, sometimes it’s unconscious. often it’s ignored because the recipient is caught unawares or afraid to call it out. we are standing up to support females across generations and will be speaking at schools and universities about what we can collectively do to promote change through how we react to habitual sexism. .
.
join the conversation and stand up with us. we are looking for guest bloggers. dm us if you’d like to be involved. .
.

text:
just saw this for some reason, it really hurt me... i never feel safe walking alone in pure daylight, never mind night time, just a few weeks ago i was leaving college and walking to the car when a car with two men stopped me to tell me how good i looked (and then they said some other horrific things) and i was terrified. i truly thought i’m that moment that i might be kidnapped and die. it makes me so sad and so angry. and now that i think of it, i’m not so sure i ever feel safe. i’m nervous when a man sits next to me and looks in my direction. i’m always extra cautious about who’s following me, and when ever i leave the house my mom reminds me to “be aware of my surroundings “. i’m always on edge. even in the gym, or just anywhere in public, where men are around me. how does everyone else feel about this? do you ever feel safe? comment below 
#feminism #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #metoo #metoomovement #womensright #rapeculture #corridorf #walkingalone #beauty #savelife #future #brightfuture #feelsafe #safetyfirst #notoworry #respectwomen #respectyourself #respect🙏 #respectothers #respecteachothers

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
no hands are tearing your soul apart anymore.
❤
no teeth are scrapping your mind to pieces.
❤
stop destroying yourself.
please.
❤
no monster is at home...no more, no more.
❤
those parts of you, that believed the bleeding tales that danced around the notes of love hurts, and the lies that shouted how abandonment and survival are life...
❤
those hands touched you were innocence should have stayed…
instead you traded cotton candy clouds for ways to survive.
you bargained for your life and closed doors from where the sun peeked to stretch it's ray's to you.
❤
i understand.
it's okay.
❤
those hands took away so much, so much that should have stayed.
innocence that should have remained untouched, pristine.
happiness should have sprouted from those corners of innocence and joy, from the tenderness of your skin, instead…
i see, you grew horns and thorns, spikes and claws.
❤
i get it.
i feel you.
❤
all too well.
all too deep.
❤
but please…
stop destroying yourself.
❤
it's been enough you know.
❤
the hatred, the hurt, the frustration…
you have kept imploding.
and all against you.
❤
you are tired.
i can see.
tired and ready to move forward, to leave that behind, to change your skin.
❤
ready.
to hug yourself.
to embrace your steps.
to own your heart.
to bless your skin.
❤
please.
no more.
stop destroying yourself.
i love you.
❤
come home.
come back.
fully...
❤
it is safe now.
come hug your body.
come hug your life.
come face existence.
rejoice in the now.
❤
no hands are pinning you down now.
no eyes are devouring you.
no words or hits are harming you.
❤
please…
stop perpetuating what they did to you.
what you learned love was, isn't.
❤
allow touch to be love again, allow touch to be safe and gentle…to be welcomed when you are ready to.
come home.
❤
stop destroying yourself.
come rejoice, come nourish and allow.
come eat and sleep and smile and dream.
❤
come, come.
come love.
❤
i love you, rejoice.
come hug life.
let life hug you.
❤
this body is home, and it's safe to embody and enjoy this existence.
❤
feel...
it is safe.
allow.
you are safe.
❤
thank you...for you.
you are home!
i love you.
namaste babe;)
❤

text:
2018 was a banner year for women in politics! 
women candidates broke records for the number of candidates for governor, u.s. house and u.s. senate. and that trend continued in the 2018 midterm elections. 
the u.s. house of representatives elected a record number of women, with at least 90 women expected to make their way to washington, d.c. in january. 
individual candidates also achieved historic firsts. democrats ilhan omar and rashida tlaib became the first muslim women elected to congress. republican marsha blackburn became tennessee’s first female senator. democrats deb haaland and sharice davids became the first native american women elected to congress. republican kristi noem became south dakota’s first female governor. -time magazine

text_retweet:
#repost @guardian
・・・
psychologist dr christine blasey ford delivered one of the most powerful testimonies in the #metoo era when she accused supreme court justice brett kavanaugh of sexual assault. she was made to relive a moment that she said "drastically altered" her life, when delivering her testimony in front of a senate judiciary committee consisting of 17 male and four female senators. ford accused kavanaugh of trying to rape her at a high school party some 30 years ago. kavanaugh, who testified after her, forcefully denied the allegation. he was ultimately confirmed in a 50 to 48 vote, with republicans supporting donald trump's pick despite extensive opposition. his nomination inflamed a deep cultural divide in today’s era of reckoning on sexual assault and harassment. ford and her family became the target of death threats, prompting the launch of a gofundme page to cover their $150,000 security costs. she recently shut down the page after raising nearly $650,000, and has pledged to donate all unused funds to charities that support trauma survivors. #thiswas2018

photos: win mcnamee/ getty images + melina mara-pool/getty images

text:
this is unusual for me... i'm usually posting beautiful pictures i took of the grace found in this world.
i know it's holiday season, i know, 'tis the season to be holly, it's the season of ends and new starts and even mistletoe kisses.
this time, i can't stop thinking about what we still need to improve, i can't stop thinking about the fact that every single day even around the most festive days of the year, there are assaults and abuse happening. and so often, the offenders are people we would not expect to do something like that. the offenders are often people we know, we trust, relatives and friends.
it's enraging thinking about the hurt that many people have to go through every day and the scars they have to carry for the rest of their lives, especially psychical ones.
it was eye opening and a really good start to see the movements of last year and we need to keep going. we need to change the way of thinking, need to show that it's never okay to hurt someone, it's never okay to do something they have not agreed to. we need to show that every person is worth to physical and psychical integrity.
i feel desperate and helpless because of this immense matter and all the structures that even begin in how the children are raised at an early age.
but it has given me hope and strength, this movement and we shall not stop.
there are thousands of thousands of stories... and everyone needs to understand and change (even though i am afraid some people never will). for may this world always be and get better.

text:
.
s h a t t e r  t h e  s i l e n c e .
❤️
so much here. 
vulnerability. courage. shame. safety.  trust. .
❤️
from brene brown - "shame is the fear of disconnection - is there something about me that if other people know it or see it that i won’t be worthy of connection?  for connection to happen we have to allow ourself to be seen. what makes us vulnerable makes us beautiful”.
.
❤️
in brene brown’s ted talk on vulnerability she talks about the meaning of courage.  she states that in latin “cor” means heart.  courage is “to tell the story of who you are with your whole heart". .
❤️
forgetting sexual abuse and then starting to remember years later as an adult was the ultimate test of learning to trust myself.  and my body. and learning many lessons around shame, vulnerability, courage, safety, trust, voice, boundaries, patience, self-compassion, self-care and so much more. .
❤️
interestingly my body "remembered" many years before my mind did. it showed up as physical issues. many authors write about this - babette rothschild, the body remembers.  the body keeps the score, bessel van der kolk.  and more. .
❤️
there was time for personal inner work. well that’s on-going, isn’t it!? lower chakra work, throat and heart too.  spiritual growth too comes out of trauma. .
❤️
so many doubts. so many questions. how could i have forgotten?  yet this is how our bodies help us get through traumatic experiences. disassociating. leaving our body at the time. and then living much of our lives in a similar state. .
disconnected. disembodied. unaware. .
our bodies and nervous system are designed to keep us safe. for the purpose of survival. it's instinct. .
❤️
yet many of us are disconnected from our instinct. our gut. we live from our heads and mind. no wonder we are constantly stressed too. .
.......continued in comments.....

text: too many cases of abuse and assault, sexual or otherwise, go unreported.. this makeup may seem shocking and extreme, but this is what both females and males go through on a daily.. this is their life, pain and fear.. i am a fan of sfx makeup and i want to use my skill and knowledge of it to raise awareness for those people who are in pain.. and yes, not all abuse is visible, it can and is mental and emotional as well as physical.. and physical abuse is most likely to be on other parts of the body, i plan to do work with that as well.. i am here for anyone who needs advice or just to talk.. if you feel in danger of threatened or you go through this, please let someone know, i know it is not easy, i know it is terrifying.. i am someone who went through a sexual assault situation.. and no my experience is not the same as anyone elses. i know that. i'm here to help and to raise awareness.. there are hotlines available 24/7, for example rainn (https://www.rainn.org/about-national-sexual-assault-telephone-hotline) they will help you if you need it.. and so will i. #metoomovement #metoo

hello. i really made this account to just discuss my interests, rant, and i also want to get back into politics and all that jazz.

an asian american activist, i'm just trying to find my identity. i would believe i'm right leaning, which is difficult to discuss with the people around me since i'm scared to talk about my opinion to others.

i hope i'm able to meet new people, discover new ideas, be able to express myself, and inspire others.
recently, i've been intrigued by japanese aesthetics. their traditional art is really cool. shoganai means "it cant be helped". and i plan on expanding that i guess.
.
.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significan notly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

tweet_full:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
there is no excuse for sexual abuse. there is no excuse for sexual abuse. there is no excuse for sexual abuse. this is the fifth submission to the survivor tree project (anonymous), and i just want to say to this survivor: i believe you. i do not think you are lying. this was was not your fault. this was not your fault. this was not your fault. •

this woman was abused at a young age by a family member with special needs. there are countless resources available on the topic of recognizing, preventing, and protecting individuals *with* disabilities from sexual abuse. rightfully so- disabled individuals are marginalized and abused at alarmingly high rates, and having these kinds of resources available is absolutely essential. but after i received this story and did some searching, i found that there are not nearly as many readily available resources on what to do if the *abuser* is a disabled individual. it’s a sensitive and multifaceted subject- in many of these cases, the abuser does not understand the concept of consent or of violating another’s personal boundaries. but. but. but. this is not an excuse for sexual assault or abuse. an abuser’s disability does not make the abused somehow obligated to put up with inappropriate behavior. in these cases, it is essential that both the abuser *and* the abused get professional intervention, if possible. this woman told her family, and they didn’t believe her. to her, i say: you are valid. you deserve love. you don’t have to go through this alone. get away from those family members, if you can. find a therapist, if you can (it’s confidential, and the best thing i have ever done for myself). if you can’t, you still have options. reach out to the survivor peer support community (see my following list for some helpful ig accounts). call the national sexual assault hotline at 1-800-656-4673, available 24/7/365. you are not alone. ✨🌱 click the link in my bio if others would like to contribute your story to the survivor tree project. #selflove #love #survivor #survivoradvocate #believesurvivors #believewomen #believeblackwomen #rapesurvivor #metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement #thesurvivortreeproject #artist

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

what is victim blaming? victim blaming is the idea that a victim was "asking for it" or that it is their fault they were raped. some examples are saying they were drunk or wearing revealing clothes. this is not true, because by definition you cannot ask for rape. it is only ever the fault of the rapist. victim blaming is a way to try to discredit victims and it is never ok.

text:
thank you genx 99.1 for having me
-
this message was to raise awareness about domestic violence but i was detailing what can lead a young girl to end up in a abusive relationship.
-
there are layers to the journey of a girl who doesn’t know about self loves and self worth.
-
it could be from a history of abuse, lack of education about themselves and what to expect as they mature, a lack of positive examples and even a lack of love shown.
-
when you live a life trying to please others due to that lack of self love, our girls will sometimes accept abuse and conform to that person’s needs because they just want to feel some kind of love.
-
young women, never sacrifice who you are to be apart of the crowd or to be in a relationship.
-
it all starts with working on loving yourself. -
there are always signs, you just have to really be present to see.
-
#saveourdaughters 
#youthspeaker 
#youthmentor 
#selflove 
#wespeaktheyspeak 
#stopdomesticviolence

text:
wow what a year 2018 has been😍our entire singer’s theatre family has worked very hard this year and it showed in our ‘beautiful’ productions (yes that was a heather’s reference). // our junior intensive was “life: the musical” and our cast full of bright, young stars wowed the audience like they always do!✨ // our senior intensive was “heather’s: the musical” and our cast of intelligent, mindful, and hardworking actors took on this dark yet humorous piece with grace and finesse.🦋 // we also got the chance to perform on 91.5 the beat twice this year! once with our heather’s cast and once again just before christmas for some carols.❤️💚 // thank you to everyone in the community who has followed along with us this year, we appreciate all the lovers of theatre and the arts that keep our company alive. we at the singer’s theatre wish you all nothing but happiness, love, and safety in 2019. 
stay tuned for more updates on our upcoming productions in 2019!!! •
•
•
•  #thesingerstheatre #kwawesome #2019 #lifethemusical #heathersthemusical #tstheathers #theatre #intensive #radio #stopabully #metoo #letstalk #neveragain

i’m glad that i can stand here today and let my soul smile again. if there’s anything i learned from this year it’s that things that feel like an ending in the moment aren’t endings, but rather the beginning (or just part of the story and neither a beginning or end). and beginning aren’t always blue skies and sunshine, but i’m really glad i’m where i am today and that i can look back and see how the hell and pain from 2017 didn’t ruin or end me, but rather was a new beginning that was a lot different than i anticipated.

nuestra responsabilidad en el año 2019 es con la verdad, la violencia de género es un flagelo que se enfrenta con investigación clara y propuestas precisas, disciplina y ética.

#repost @ateneoecologico (@get_repost)
・・・
tal y como estaba programado dentro del plan integral de prevención de la violencia contra las mujeres #agendabolivar se trabajó en los términos de referencia para construir la encuesta regional de violencia basada en género para el estado bolívar lo cual es un hito en este tipo de investigación y vendría a completar los estudios estadísticos que el ateneo ecológico a través de su programa #observatorioguayanesdegenero ha realizado desde el año 2015. de esta manera, luego del trabajo de consultoría con la doctora @irenecasique de #unammx los equipos del ateneo y @unfpa_venezuela decidieron incorporar al equipo de expertos del @ciepv_guayana y @cisorredsoc con el fin de que se construyera el cuestionario, se validara a nivel técnico y se llevara a campo, trabajo que determinará la aplicación a gran escala para el año 2019

#ateneoecologicodelorinoco #unfpa #unfpavenezuela #ciepv #cisor #rednaranja #onumujeres #metoo #metoovenezuela

text:
pause and take time to reflect on your 2018.

grab your journal and write down your most memorable 2018 moments, your biggest “2018 hits” - interesting encounters, major breakthroughs, joyful experiences, new business endeavours, challenges you overcame, travels, amazing new connections, deep self-discoveries.

focus on your wins - big or small - doesn’t matter.

anything that makes you feel more grounded, excited, connected, in your power.

now...i realize that not all your 2018 experiences might have been blissful...that you may still have pain lingering and regrets from those experiences.

but you fought through them and proved to yourself that you’re resilient and powerful!

acknowledge and celebrate that! 💎

yes, you are powerful, capable, and amazing.

let your “2018 hits” list be a reminder to yourself of your awesomeness. 
i believe in you! ✨

love,
millen livis 💖

text:
if there is anything we can learn from all the sexual abuse that has been exposed over the past few years it is this: 
denying the risk only increases risk. 
the most professional, educated, and likable perpetrators are most likely to be protected by their peers. 
choosing to believe a child and take action to protect them is worth it - every time. it can, literally, save hundreds of lives. 
not educating children about body safety doesn’t protect their innocence, it makes them more vulnerable. 
sexual abuse has been and continues to be an epidemic, that affects all demographics, all institutions, and is still, most common within the family unit with juveniles being one of the biggest segments of perpetrators of child sexual abuse. 
it’s not a matter of *can* we prevent sexual abuse, but if we’re willing.

text:
2018’s biggest “i can’t believe this happened” moment - hosting the viatec awards at the royal theatre. for someone with social anxiety, who always considered herself to be shitty at public speaking, struggles with memorization and is not at peace with her body, getting up to host this show in front of 1000 tech industry colleagues, friends and strangers was the most terrifying professional move i’ve made to date. it took a year of events, including grownups read things they wrote as kids, confabulation, my first ever standup comedy set and a fuckup night to get to the point i could stand on a stage and do this. most importantly, i made a statement about our industry’s need for change in the era of #metoo and #timesup that scared the hell out of me and was relieved by the mostly positive reaction. i was fortunate to work with an incredible team from @viatec to support and guide me to ensure all went well. and i think it did. 
overall, it was a lesson in pushing against self-imposed boundaries and going big when it would have been so much easier to say no. so much gratitude tied into all of this for all those who believed in me when i didn’t. 
#2018 #reflections #wow #bigyear #overwhelmed #hosting #publicspeaking #pushyourself #womenintech #tech #yyj #gratitude #socialanxiety #boundaries #pushyourlimits #daringgreatly #sayyes #emcee #goforit

text:
#rp #growtheheckup 📺 planned parenthood is black genocide.

in new york city, thousands more black babies are aborted than born alive each year, and the abortion rate among black mothers is more than three times higher than it is for white mothers. according to a city health department report released in may, between 2012 and 2016 black mothers terminated 136,426 pregnancies and gave birth to 118,127 babies. by contrast, births far surpassed abortions among whites, asians and hispanics.

nationally, black women terminate pregnancies at far higher rates than other women. 
in 2014, 36% of all abortions were performed on black women, who are just 13% of the female population.
.
.
#abortion #believewomen #blacklivesmatter #timesup #metoo #plannedparenthood #healthcare #moms #blackcommunity #criminaljustice #prisonreform #injustice

text:
片付けてるのか拡げてるのか💦

たまにバルサンを焚く。去年はそのままにしてたんで念入りに。近況をほとんどupしなかった１年、リアルに更新した半年。慌ただしい中でも努めて自分の『現時点でのホント』に忠実でいた。全部が全部じゃないけど、正直さを恐れず発信すること、抱え持った気持ちの純度を保持したまま、文章に落とした。

それをしなかったら、何に対しても強くてhealthyな愛情が持てない。控えめにしているだけが謙遜ではないし、なんにしてもそうやけど正しく模倣することだけに長けて、独自の考えを持たないことをhealthyと言わないから。自と他の区別を。私は私、なのである。

in  or out、身近なものごとの関係性を見直す年だった。流行ったんで私も。

#metoo そして、 #change へ。

text:
i am beginning the last day of this year in one of my favourite yoga postures - sitting upright in front of my lap top, hands on the keys, steaming cup of tea to the right, ocean view to the left.

i am so struck by the collective voice i have heard and witnessed closing down this year. i don’t remember ever hearing the refrain “thank god that’s over” united so strongly before.  even the mighty in my world - super successful online positivity-get-the-life-you-want-etc giants - are taking time to show the cracks and the wounds and declare 2018 as a year that broke them (of course they are rising now, thank goodness!). as someone who has taken years to identify as a writer simply because i write rather than measuring the validity of this identification by the fame or income connected to it - i am compelled to add my voice.  and yet i find myself hesitating. our natural human urge to share our hearts, to be witnessed and seen feels as though it has been pushed into monstrous distorted shapes these past few years as the exponential speed and reach of online exhibitionism has heated up.  sharing or witnessing another, it all feels so heightened, heated and intense lately.  many of us clamour for attention in the clanging silence of overcrowded noisy virtual spaces. others wait in the shadows, poisoned darts flying from our keyboards, taking advantage of the open vulnerability others are willing to display. 
and so i seek to find my centre and my place in all this.  i remember my feminist mothers (yes i had many) teaching me many years ago - “the personal is the political mira”. and so it is.  i believe wholeheartedly in the contradiction that we must take personal responsibility to calm, to centre and to heal knowing full well that the reasons we may be so agitated, un-centred and wounded are in large part the result of the inequities and traumas the collective presses down onto and into us; that while our story is ours alone to own, we only heal in connection with others; that healing may be a quiet private affair or a loud, proud public declaration of what happened or both; that each of us walks our own path but we are undeniably “us”.

text:
2018 was a one hell of a roller coaster ride. you see, earlier this year and even before i am one of those people who will probably ask sexually assaulted people, why didn't you fought back? why didn't you shouted?

i always remind myself that if it's gonna happen to me i'm gonna fight back. i'm gonna shout at the top of my lungs so i can get everybody's attention.

but on the night of february 24, 2018 i was proven wrong. i stood frozen when some random guy grabbed my boobs out of nowhere. i just stood there for a good minute, legs are so weak it's like they are turning into liquid. i couldn't find the voice to shout, it's like my voicebox disappeared into oblivion, never to come back.

all i could do that time was to dissolved in tears and shook so violently i thought my internal organs will get tangled up with each other.

i keep asking myself, are we suppose to get used to this? do i have to accept the fact that this is normal? in a woman's life, this is going to be a part of her everyday life. catcalls, men grabbing your boobs or butt. is that gonna be a part of our everyday lives?

no, it sure hell will never be. this 2019, i'm gonna fight back. i'm gonna fight the hell out. i'm gonna slap, kick, punch every catcallers i will meet. i'm gonna make them realize that not because we have a vagina between our thighs makes us weak. having to bleed every month and not die and to bring out a human out of it, it sure as hell do not make us weak.

2019, watch the hell out.

#metoo

text:
i've been sitting here thinking about the last 60 days .  i lost a total of 5 family members and friends including my older sister who was just laid to rest less than 2 weeks ago and it hurt bad but i kept going , kept smiling and gave myself permission to grieve when i felt like it was safe .

have you been there ? 
have you ever built a wall that needs to be torn down so that you can authentically connect with people assigned to push you into purpose and build real relationships with ? #metoo 
in my first workbook be b.r.a.v.e , the b=break the ice with other powerful women . and that's hard (at least for me) when you've been hurt & disappointed before but i learned that if you are honest, open and  intentional you'll find purpose & prayer partners ,  confidants & co-laborers in the most unusual places . 
don't dismiss the situation or site of where god wants you to #build again . it's ok to #bebrave , build relationships that will push you to bloom. 
sn-i changed the cover to a more confident , connected me 🙌

this photo holds a lot of emotion and has taken me a long time to post. and i’m scared shitless to share. 
the main reason i struggle to post this is because i have people in my life that with have alopecia or are going through chemotherapy and i don’t want it to come across in any way that i am not grateful for my hair.
for me this is something very personal and has been an emotional struggle. a few months back i changed my hair colour and when i sent pictures or people saw me in person, everyone seemed to like it. 
i needed a change as i was about to turn 40 and head back to nashville. for those that have followed me for some time you know that the last three years have been a real tornado. i felt i was marking on a new chapter of my life and wanted change. now i have to note, my stylist did an incredible job and the colour turned out great (in this picture it shows lighter). i wanted red to honour my grandma. 
i had no idea what darkening my hair would do or the triggers it would bring up. 
it was pretty instantly; pretty much the next morning when i awoke and looked in the mirror at the reflection i saw i felt off, distant. 
back in 2012 i cut my hair off for charity and eventually i went blonde and never looked back!
the problem was the marriage i was in was extremely abusive and it seemed to get worse when it came to my appearance. i could only wear certain things, act a certain way, get to a certain size before he was clear what he liked and disapproved of. 
so when he “gave me permission” to cut my hair, it was only expected that after a certain amount of time i was to grow it back out. i continued to cut my hair shorter and his patience grew thin. i was told “you can keep it blonde, though i like it darker; but we had an agreement that you grow it back long. it’s what i prefer.” when i eventually left the relationship lets just say my hair became something so precious to me. i shaved the sides one time and continued to cut to short lengths and play with my blonde side. it was so much more than hair; it was an identity that i felt i lost so long ago. crazy as it sounds; blonde feels like home to me💗
continue in comments below #keepingitreal

-usually my comics are supposed to be funny and comical, however, i realized that with this platform, i have the opportunity to spread more important messages like self acceptance and equality. being a teenager myself, i know what it feels like to constantly compare yourself to others on social media. and if you think about it, social media is set up to compare ourselves to one another through the number of followers, likes, and comments on posts. although social media is a great way to connect people together, it can also be toxic by influencing one to idealize false beauty standards set by celebrities who use photoshop and other self-editing softwares. through this comic, i want to bring awareness to not only harmful comparisons, but these unrealistic beauty standards. i hope this comic helps some one out there realize that not everything on social media is real and to accept themselves for who they are - i love you all much and hope that you love yourself too❤️ #intersectionalfeminism #pride #feminism #femfam #feminist #feminismtag #blm #immigrantsmakeamericagreat #notmypresident #activist #blacklivesmatter #ally #lgbtq #socialjustice #loveislove #lovewins #activist #activism #defenddaca #takeaknee #metoo #neveragain #enough

text:
the art of organizing

these past 7 years i've had the honor of working with a lot of community organizers. being tough times there's a lot of issues affecting people and with each issue you see many people stepping up to the plate. like with any other field there's a lot of great organizers, some who shouldn't be in organizing and a rare few who have the passion, tact and determination to bring fellow organizers together for the greater good. 
like with any movement this year we needed a lot of help for the start of #shedoes. that came for us through @carlosthemailman. carlos is no stranger to anyone involved in organizing or politics in la. when it comes to the main issues affecting the people he is always there. not only involved, he brings a ton of help and can bring awareness to your organization or cause. like he did for our #shedoes movement, i've seen him bring solid support to countless other movements in la.

from #housing to #healthcare to #homelessness, #publicbanking, #keepfamiliestogether, helping puerto rico, #metoo, #burlingtonunidos, yes on 10, for our teachers, helping great candidates win, to the front of the fight at #standingrock, carlos has been there. anyone organizing in la knows that if and when you need help, or when you need sound advice, you can always count on carlos.

these last few months were tough for carlos. he was in and out of the hospital. you won't see that on facebook, neither will you see him missing an event where he promised to be there. when others give a million excuses as to why they can't, carlos will always be true to his word. a master in tact and at heart, he is everywhere!

we all know the housing situation in la looks bleak. with rental rates continuing to rise it's affecting everyone. to push the issue to the forefront carlos has organized an amazing march at the rose parade on tuesday the 1st of 2019. things do look bleak for the new year but we have people like carlos fighting for us. he was there for us, now we need to be there for him to fight for fair and affordable housing in la!

#shedoes deserve shelter and protection!

event link: https://www.facebook.com/events/244908046134128/?ti=cl
name: Mel Tillekeratne

we all know the housing situation in la looks bleak. with rental rates continuing to rise it is affecting everyone. to push the issue to the forefront carlos has organized an amazing march at the rose parade on tuesday the 1st of 2019. things do look bleak for the new year but we have people like carlos fighting for us. he was there for us, now we need to be there for him to fight for fair and affordable housing in la!

 deserve shelter and protection!

text:
i lived abroad for 2 years, it’s already scary to live alone so far away from home. i couldn’t afford a flat for my self so i shared a room with a guy, he had a girlfriend and the girlfriend also moved in, so i felt kind of safe for a while.
after 1 year, things started to get shady, i missed so many signs, he started to try to control everything in my life, i thought i might be mistaken since the girlfriend was still living there, but then they broke up, he started to control me with fear, i thought he was going to kill me.
i got out of that flat, lucky enough i found another one available, but he kept finding me and following me and trying to intimidate me.
i left the country and came back home. 
i finally feel safe after 6 months. .
.
.

text:
we’re counting down the final hours of 2018 @girledworld and finding many reasons to count the wins for women and girls of the world this year. .

this was the year that saw: ➖women across the world unite, stand up and rise to the #metoo and #timesup movements ✔️
➖an unprecedented number of women speaking out and stepping up to catalyse record-breaking political races and social change ✔️
➖a series of historic firsts including #spain appointing a majority-women cabinet ✔️
➖voters in ireland striking down one of the most draconian #abortion bans in the developed world ✔️
➖women in saudi arabia able to drive legally ✔️
➖female candidates breaking historic ground in the us midterm elections and @michelleobama findjng her powerful voice✔️
➖iranian women watching the #worldcup in a sports stadium alongside men for the first time ✔️
➖new zealand prime minister #jacindaardern making history as the second elected head of state to give birth while in office, and first elected leader ever to take maternity leave proving it is indeed possible to be both a prime minister and mum ✔️✔️
➖the #nobelpeace prize awarded jointly to denis mukwege, a congolese surgeon who treats rape victims, and nadia murad, an iraqi woman and member of the yazidi religious minority who was captured by isis and is now an activist advocating for victims of sex trafficking, and the first iraqi woman to receive the award ✔️ .
➖ and among countless other extraordinary ordinary moments of women and girls standing up, stepping up and speaking out, without knowing it possibly, without claiming it, so too, they have advanced the causes, opportunities and rights of all women and girls, and in their honour, we @girledworld would like to thank them and thank you for being part of what made our 2018 rock, and leave you with the powerful wisdom of @drmayaangelou to give you fuel for 2019. .

may 2019 be the year of your becoming 👊🏽
#nye2019 #girledworld .
.
illustration via the talented @kimothy.joy 
#standup #girledworld

text:
i was planning on making a really cliche “end of 2018” post about growth and finishing school etc, but i learnt something today that has changed my mind. i’m not going to sit here and blab about how thankful i am for everything because the truth is i’m not. there are a lot of things that i am not grateful for, some of which i refuse to stay quiet about any longer. i’m not grateful that i left wangaratta high school 18 months ago and people are still telling lies/believing lies about me. so i’m here to tell my truth and set the record straight. today i learnt that a certain individual (if you’re familiar with this story you’ll know who i’m talking about) has been telling people that the reason that we are no longer talking is because i blamed all of my problems on other people. to be perfectly honest, he’s partly correct; i did blame some of my problems on him. the reason for this, however, is that my problem was trying to cope with being sexually assaulted, and i blamed him because he was the one who did it. i don’t care if no one believes me anymore. anyone who still thinks this is my fault and believes his bullshit lies please feel free to unfollow me/never talk to me again because i don’t want people like you in my life anymore. and i’m not afraid to say it anymore because it isn’t my fault. i didn’t ask for it; quite the opposite actually, and i have nothing to be ashamed of.
to end this on a cliche i’m incredibly grateful for my gal pals for sticking by me and always believing (in) me. you girls are incredible and i love you so much. happy end of 2018 and thanks for coming to my tedtalk #metoo
