text:
#confession of 2018: since everyone only share happy events of their lives and their accomplishments, i thought to share my failures or at least one failure which defined most of my 2018 in a good way (or at least i think it is good). so in 2017, friends and family talked me out of my major apprehensions regarding relationships and i decided that yes, i won’t mind getting married. getting a green signal, a friend quickly introduced me to someone, i liked him and we immediately started going out. for first few months, everything was happy and amazing but at the end of 2017, everything turned bad. i was going through hell at work, as my the-then boss was making the workplace extremely uncomfortable for me and i took a stand by speaking about it (yes, #metoo). under duress, i was having emotionally weak moments and i had a minor accident too. while i was going through all of that, i realised that he wasn’t there, as someone who actually should have been there. fine that i am an independent woman and i have lived alone and i can handle shit but then why would i need to be with someone if i can’t count on him in my weak moments and/or i would need to think so much to just make a call or drop a message to that person, do i need him? with this thought, i entered 2018 and the first thing i did in 2018 was to sort that mess. i said goodbye to him. the efforts he made in the following days were enough consolation for me for taking that decision. i won’t lie, there were times when i got weaker and/or i thought i am being egotistic and i dropped him a text. thankfully, it didn’t work but what made me realise was that i need to hold all of them close to my heart who have been there, despite my shortcomings. i made a conscious effort to stay in touch with them and be thankful to them or i apologised to them if and when there was a need. i stopped people from taking me for granted. and so on and so forth.
.
.
.
this ‘equilibrist on one arm’ by jorge marist, displayed at the hyder aliyev center is a true depiction of my life in 2018. i have grown to be so different today that i can look at any kind of danger in the eye. i am ready to embrace 2019. #happynewyear
name: Maria Patel

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
вот таким был 2018🎑
.
.
уходящий год был перенасыщен событиями: минирование верховой рады, автокефалия упц, историческая встреча ким чен ына и мун чжэ ина, не менее историческая встреча ким чен ына и трампа, олимпиада в пхёнчхане и российские атлеты под нейтральным флагом, «сага о солсберецком шпиле» и много-много санкций, химическая атака в думе, которая была или, может быть, нет, скандал с cambridge analytica и допрос цукерберга в конгрессе, запуск falcon heavy c tesla roadster на борту, извержения вулканов и цунами, выпуск национальной криптовалюты в венесуэле, падение биткоина, трагедия в кемерово, стрельба в школе во флориде, убийство джамаля хашогжи, после которого мир вспомнил, что в йемене люди умирают от голода и холеры, «жёлтые жилеты», уход меркель с поста главы правящей партии фрг, успешная посадка insight на марсе, чёрный дельфин, который умер, потому что съел несколько десятков пакетов, первый ребёнок с «отредактированным» днк, военное положение в стране, вакарчук и зеленский в президентском рейтинге (кстати, кто не смотрел, рекомендую к просмотру интервью гордону зеленского и коломойского), невероятные финальные поединки на #rollandgaross.... и это только то, что сразу приходит в голову. .🧗‍♂️🧗‍♂️🧘‍♀️
.
нас всех поднимало и бросало, и чаще всё-таки бросало, но мы старались сохранять позитив и вместе с этим прислушиваться к себе, потому что «посмотри, что происходит вокруг, будь честным с собой, хорошенько подумай, где ты, кто ты и чем хочешь заниматься, это не шутки, давно уже пора...»
.
точно могу сказать, что в этом году старательно слушала свой authentic voice и пыталась быть максимально искренней с собой. всё, что мешало и тянуло вниз, ушло безвозвратно, а действительно важное вышло на первый план, пришла определённость и теперь кажется, что стоишь перед белым холстом.
.

.

text: 2018 was fucked in every way possible but at the end of the evening i’m still here, in the flesh, i stopped many bad habits this year and i’ve stepped outside of my comfort zone, i’ve explored my body, my mind and my style. i’ve gone back to looking how i want to, i’ve stopped depriving myself of nutrients and started trying to encourage people to voice their thoughts. i’ve done and seen things, i’ve fallen out of and back into love and i’m thankful for any and every human that stood by my side this year regardless of whether or not they still stand there. i love my family, friends and girlfriend, i love that there’s now an app to help prevent teen suicide, i love that #metoo helped people speak up and i love that people were kind fucking humans this year despite the odd few bad grapes in the bunch. fuck 2018, here’s to a slightly upgraded and peaceful 2019. hopefully. we’ll find out in 365 days i guess 😉

text:
a year in review would not be complete without a mention of illinois senator tammy duckworth.  this spring, duckworth, 50, became the first senator to give birth while in office. on april 18, senators voted unanimously to allow infants on the floor during votes, reversing a rule that prohibited family members. that same day, duckworth brought her 10-day-old daughter, maile pearl bowlsbey, as she voted against confirming james bridenstine as nasa’s next administrator. 
having a baby at 50 shows you can’t have it all.  i had my kids later in life because i made the choice early in my career that women shouldn't to have to make. i was in my 20s and trying to rise through the ranks of the military, i knew if i took time off to get pregnant and raise my children, it would limit my career. when they’re climbing the ladder, so many young women have to make this decision. they go on the mommy track because we don’t have the structures in place to support them. 
one support is paid family leave.  duckworth is cosponsoring senator kirsten gillibrand’s [d-ny] bill. it’s based on kind of an insurance model, where you would contribute the equivalent of $2.50 a week and it would provide 12 weeks of paid family leave. and the employer would pay $3 a week. it’s very reasonable, it’s self-directed, it’s people helping themselves, and it just makes sense. 
on the cusp of being passed is the friendly airports for mothers (fam) act.  the fam act would require all medium and large airports, which would be over 90 percent of the airports in this country, to provide safe lactation rooms for moms. -marie claire

these are solutions that are both fair and make sense.  good things are happening!  we can't wait to hear her next great ideas!  #womeninpolitics #womenleadership #womeningovernment #nastywomen #genderequality #metoo #timesup #womensmarch #womenvote #womenswave #whyimarch #imarchfor #equality #womensrights #feminism #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #intersectional #futureisfemale #femaleempowerment #girlsrule #girlsruntheworld #girlboss #ladyboss #ovarygang #girlpower #grlpower #womensupportingwomen #eeoc #diversity

tweet_full:
a year in review would not be complete without a mention of illinois senator tammy duckworth.  this spring, duckworth, 50, became the first senator to give birth while in office. on april 18, senators voted uimously to allow infants on the floor during votes, reversing a rule that prohibited family members. that same day, duckworth brought her 10-day-old daughter, maile pearl bowlsbey, as she voted against confirming james bridenstine as nasa’s next administrator. 
having a baby at 50 shows you can’t have it all.  i had my kids later in life because i made the choice early in my career that women should not to have to make. i was in my 20s and trying to rise through the ranks of the military, i knew if i took time off to get pregt and raise my children, it would limit my career. when they’re climbing the ladder, so many young women have to make this decision. they go on the mommy track because we don’t have the structures in place to support them. 
one support is paid family leave.  duckworth is cosponsoring senator kirsten gillibrand’s [d-ny] bill. it’s based on kind of an insurance model, where you would contribute the equivalent of $2.50 a week and it would provide 12 weeks of paid family leave. and the employer would pay $3 a week. it’s very reasonable, it’s self-directed, it’s people helping themselves, and it just makes sense. 
on the cusp of being passed is the friendly airports for mothers (fam) act.  the fam act would require all medium and large airports, which would be over 90 percent of the airports in this country, to provide safe lactation rooms for moms. -marie claire

these are solutions that are both fair and make sense.  good things are happening!  we can not wait to hear her next great ideas!  #womeninpolitics #womenleadership #womeningovernment #nastywomen #genderequality #metoo #timesup #womensmarch #womenvote #womenswave #whyimarch #imarchfor #equality #womensrights #feminism #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #intersectional #futureisfemale #femaleempowerment #girlsrule #girlsruntheworld #girlboss #ladyboss #ovarygang #girlpower #grlpower #womensupportingwomen #eeoc #diversity

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied. 
in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
manasi pradhan is an author and poet who received the rani lakshmibai stree shakti puraskar in 2013 for her work in fighting for women rights. born to a poor family in the state of odisha, she travelled 15 km daily to the only school in the entire region. she was the first woman from her village to earn a law degree. she has won many accolades including the ‘outstanding women award’ in 2011 from the united nation’s un women and national commission for women. she is the founder of nirbhaya vahini and oyss women and head the honour for women national campaign, a nationwide movement to end violence against women in india. she is also serving on the panel of central board of film certification (censor board) for india. she is a member of the international governing council of world women organization (wwo) and inquiry committee of the national commission for women. she was awarded with the stree shakti puraskar in 2013 by the former president mr pranab mukherjee.
.
.
in 2014, the honour for women national campaign headed by manasi pradhan released a four-point charter of demand for all state governments of india:

1. complete clamp down on liquor trade
2. self-defense training for women as part of educational curriculum
3. special protection force for women security in every district
4. fast-track court and special investigating & prosecuting wing for crime against women in every district. the charter forms a cornerstone of the movement and has led several state governments to make suitable amendments.
.
she is an inspiration for many and a role model for all of us.
. 
sources: yourstory & wikipedia

text:
the year ends with a warm meal and a fine book to read. what more could a girl want!

reflecting on the year that went by, i see a lot of positive events that have happened. the dilution of section 377, the fury of #metoo movement, the criminalising of triple talaq among many other. although the critiques might point out to me that there have been a high number of disastrous events too and i duly acknowledge it, but we cannot fail to recognise the history that is being made and the huge turn of events that has been happening to help progress humanity.

forgive me, if i want to end this year on a happier note and believe in the fact that 2018 has been a good year, that there still resides kindness in us, that the marginalised sections of this society will receive their dues, that education and food and shelter will reach one and all and that we have hope of saving humankind.

text:
hey 2018, wanna know what you taught me? you taught me i still have a crush on chewbacca and also a new one on james comey.
_
you taught me that the world is filled with intelligent, conscious and positive people, who live with truth and hope. 
_
you taught me that when you literally and figuratively fall, you get up to become stronger, happier and feeling pretty kick ass. 
_
you taught me that my uno game is truly better than ever!!
_
you taught me that there’s a seemingly endless myriad of self-absorbed jerks in the world - and that in stark contrast to this, it is the conscious, selfless and positive people on which i’m focused and to whom i tip my metaphorical hat. 
_
you taught me how much i love my family. 
_
you taught me to remain the antithesis of hyperbole. 
_
you taught me how much i still love coffee. 
_
and finally, you’ve taught me that tonight, i will drink my body weight in champagne. 
_
happy new year to the non-jerks out there!! i hope 2019 brings you more love, more positivity and more dogs on beaches!
_

text: 2018: et år med så mange oplevelser og tiltag at jeg ikke kunne huske det hele. for der har været meget! noget skidt og rigtig rigtig meget godt... jeg har doneret æg til endnu et par som forhåbentlig får en skøn baby i maven i løbet af 2019. jeg har præget med min stemme bla. i jyllandsposten og i fagbladet dap. jeg har fået lov til at pryde en masse ungers hverdag med nogle af de tiltag jeg har drømt om at kunne røre ved. jeg har desværre været ude for at kunne skrive #metoo som alt for mange mennesker har. jeg er blevet ansat som psykomotorisk konsulent. en fornem titel der ikke var indregnet i mine drømme. jeg har mødt en mand der mærkes som hjem💥 jeg laver altid en taknemmelighedsliste. at kunne se nedskrevet og samlet hvor mange ting året har bragt med sig visuelt, er en god ting for mig.💥 i år har jeg valgt at lave en liste der også beskriver den indre taknemmelighed. den skal laves i dag. ting som at få tættere relation til min familie, at ses mere med min mindste søster, at tillægge sig viden om ens styrke i efter et knæk, at kunne holde fast i ens venskaber trods voksendommens travlhed og lille plads tilbage er et par af de hjertesager der kommer på listen. 💥 jeg laver også en liste for 2019. med mit nytårsfokus. frem for at love mig selv at gøre fysiske ting, vil jeg hellere blive bevidst om hvor mit fokus skal være. som regl er det væk fra det der stresser mig eller ikke længere tjener mig og hen på det der giver mig energi, ro og luft i lungerne. i år 2019 vil mit fokus være meget på mig. at komme tilbage til mig og blomstre derfra. der har været så mange fantastiske oplevelser i 2018 men med det også så meget stimuli som trak opmærksomheden væk fra mit kropslige hjem. ‘19 bliver et år med ny viden håber jeg. og et år med fokus rettet mod de ting jeg ved er gode for mig. søvn, rar mad, dybe vejrtrækninger, masser af kærlighed og sex. egenomsorg og omsorg for dem jeg holder af hvis der er energi og overskud til det i hjemmet (mig). jeg kan mærke at 2019 bliver et godt og blomstrende år. og at starte året ud med en fyr der har vendt op og ned på alt og retter fokus på nuet og vil en det bedste? det er den bedste start for mig på året 2019.
name: Ea Fleron

text:
2018, what a year!
📈in sweden the politics has been a huge part of 2018. the highest voting participation since 1985 and the parties spent so much money on their campaigns.
greta thunberg, environmental activist, only 15 years old spoke to the world in poland during the climate meeting in katowice. her words has spread across the world and lots of people with influence has supported her.
. 🔥the extremely hot summer lead to severe wildfires and draught that effected us pretty badly. however, with help from all over europe we managed to control them and save a lot of forrest as well as people.
.
⚽️besides politics sweden managed to get into the quarterfinals in vm (soccer), something we haven’t done since 1994!
.
📻something that’s also quite interesting is foreign media and news services reporting about no-go zones and rape in certain parts of sweden. news that, in most cases are completely nonsense and shown from one perspective. if you look at the statistics, sweden have never had a lower rate when it comes to deadly violence and the equality is on real progress after #metoo
.
🎼 in april abba announced that they’ve recorded two new songs, the first they’ve made since their breakup in 1982. the songs will be released next year.
.
finally,i would like to wish you happy new year and i look forward to continue telling you people about sweden. next year i will start with a theme week called “sweden through time” where i’ll tell you about major historical events
once again, happy new year! gott nytt år!🎉

text:
with 2018 nearing to an end, i felt like this was something everybody should hear and believe. 2018 has been a crazy year, no doubt. i've had my ups and downs but with 2019 looming ahead, i can safely say that i managed to get through all the pain and the joy that this year has brought me. at the moment, most things seemed like the end of the world and i could not think past that one failure but, now looking back on it, it feels like just another conundrum amidst many. i'm proud of myself for standing my ground through all that and i feel everyone else should be equally proud for living through another messy year. 2018, while, somewhat pain inducing, has also been a year where social movements have progressed rapidly and that's something to be joyful about. so many rape victims have come forward to claim justice, transgenders were finally given identity cards in pakistan, women were issued driving licenses in saudi arabia. with so much more hope for these movements, 2019 can only bring an even more rapid progress and change. happy new year!
.

.
.
.
.
.

name: Feminist
tweet_full:
with 2018 nearing to an end, i felt like this was something everybody should hear and believe. 2018 has been a crazy year, no doubt. i have had my ups and downs but with 2019 looming ahead, i can safely say that i managed to get through all the pain and the joy that this year has brought me. at the moment, most things seemed like the end of the world and i could not think past that one failure but, now looking back on it, it feels like just another conundrum amidst many. i am proud of myself for standing my ground through all that and i feel everyone else should be equally proud for living through another messy year. 2018, while, somewhat pain inducing, has also been a year where social movements have progressed rapidly and that's something to be joyful about. so many rape victims have come forward to claim justice, transgenders were finally given identity cards in pakistan, women were issued driving licenses in saudi arabia. with so much more hope for these movements, 2019 can only bring an even more rapid progress and change. happy new year!
.
. .
.
.
.
.
.
#feminism #feminist #womenempowerment #powertothewomen #girlpower #unabashedlyshameless #newyear #pain #joy #hopeful #change #2019 #justice #metoo #socialmovements #loveyourself #happynewyear

text:
#metoo #niunamas 
i am a daughter, i am a sister, i am a cousin, i am a friend, i am a women, i am... en un abrir y cerrar de ojos lo que antes era musa ahora es objeto, lo que antes era templo ahora es sexo. tu ves desnudes, yo veo arte.  la cantidad de ropa que tengo no define la cantidad de respeto que merezco. muchos miran pero no ven. y ahi viene el problema que ha pasado desde el comienzo de nuestra existencia, donde la humanidad piensa que tiene el derecho de criticar, abusar, herir, maltratar solo por lo que tengo o por lo que ven. cansa tener que caminar por las calles con miedo, tener que velar lo que me pongo, digo, pienso, porque provocó o te insulta, cansa tener que velar donde salgo, con quien, y la hora, porque hay mas gente que quiere hacer mas mal que bien, cuando debe de haber mas gente que haga el bien y no el mal. cansa tener que ver en las redes, noticias, periódicos, mundo, de personas que fueron matadas, maltratadas y violadas.
cansa tener que vivir con la mirada de que soy carne en vez de que soy diosa. ojo, esto no significa que hay que vivir sin malicia, al contrario, la malicia tiene que ser la base. pero el problema no es mi ropa, el problema es tu mentalidad. el problema no es mi traje muy corto o muy largo, es tu forma de sexualizar, el problema no es que me lo busque, es tu atrevimiento de faltarme el respeto, el problema no soy yo, eres tu. el problema no es la mujer ni el hombre que pasan por esta situación, es que la sociedad desea hechar la culpa, hacer silencio, dar la otra cara y hacer que no vio nada. 
#unidossomosmasfuertes #añonuevo #queenn #blessed

text:
🐺 que no se te olvide: esta manada aúlla más fuerte que la vuestra.
✊💜✊
________ .
.
🦊 encontrarte con esta frase enfrente del ministerio de justicia y pensar que no podría estar en un lugar mejor.
.
.
. 🦊 hoy quería dejar esta foto porque cuando piense en el 2018 también recordaré el 8m, nos recordaré a todas juntas, gritando a la vez "yo sí te creo" y se me pondrán de nuevo los pelos de punta al ver una marea que no terminaba en las calles de madrid y toda españa.
recordaré que nosotras somos la manada. que queremos ser libres, no valientes.
🔸 en 2019 seguiremos saliendo a la calle, reclamaremos igualdad, no vamos a dejar que nos quiten los derechos que ya hemos conseguido (recordad salir a votar siempre, por favor). .
.
.
🦊 de 2018 recordaré los podcast de @barbijaputaaa con un montón de inspiración, mujeres fuertes y valientes, los geniales artículos de @desireebela , los viajes en metro leyendo...
.
.
. 🦊 en 2018 por primera vez en mi vida dije "mi marido". porque los hombres buenos son nuestros aliados y él es el mejor compañero de viaje. .
.
.
🦊 fue nuestra primera vez en asia. caminamos por la gran muralla y recorrimos japón, con cientos de momentos inolvidables.
.
.
.
🦊también recordaré a las personas que no han querido estar a mi lado en mi año más difícil. no ha sido fácil necesitar  abrazos y palabras de ánimo cuando estaba, literalmente, sin energía física y emocional,  encontrar malos gestos y silencios. termino 2018 sin rencor y desprendiéndome de ellas, deseándoles lo mejor en la vida. .
.
.
🦊 recordaré 2018 como el año en el que conocí virtualmente a una comunidad que me ha dado consejos, cariño, ánimo y fuerza aún sin darse cuenta. #diabetesp 💉gracias a todos vosotros que publicais vuestro  día a día con diabetes tipo 1. juntos damos visibilidad y a la vez quitamos protagonismo a la diabetes.
_______
🦊 2018: has sido dolor, tristeza, inspiración, aprendizaje, crecimiento, aceptación, emoción, felicidad... no has sido un año perfecto pero lo que es seguro es que no te vamos a olvidar.
✨
✨
feliz 2019 a todos y a vuestras familias de corazón. 🥂
.

2018 has been a very interesting year. lots of ups and downs yet i feel like i've truly grown as a person and with my business. some major highlights - got to visit paris and amsterdam with @sreenag and @gearheadvyx. this break was much needed and was unforgettable. worked with aweosme clients like @dakshinachitra_heritagemuseum @kalpanarts @srinivasan2728 @chennaiphotobiennale @playadishakti to name just a few. got to visit telengana weavers and really see all the magic happen thanks to @narasimhanvenkatesh. visited for the first time @zeejlf, started the #margazhi updates blog and probably the biggest highlight for me is pulling off the #metoo themed #golu. each year i wonder how i'm going to outdo the previous one but some how it all works out thanks to @sreenag @sajjige @nagarajanroopa @brramkumar so.. fingers crossed! happy new year everybody!
. .
.
.
.

ett händelserikt år närmar sig sitt slut och dörren till 2019 står på glänt. 
demokratibygget blickar framåt mot ett spännande år med nya idéer, samarbeten och insatser för en stark demokrati. det blir eu-val och möjlighet att lyfta demokratifrågor kopplat till internationellt samarbete. vi gläds också över att vi med stöd från regeringens satsning efter #metoo-uppropen, kommer att erbjuda kostnadsfri kompetensutveckling för att motverka sexuella trakasserier i skolan. är din skola intresserad? hör av dig!

tillsammans bygger vi demokratin! vi ses 2019✨

text:
though my health hasn’t been the best this year (currently not feeling well), i still had an eventful year. i’m grateful for the “push through”. i’m grateful to god for giving me the strength & the right attitude to get through some rough times. i’m getting teary just thinking about the encouragement from my village this year, i’m grateful for them. all that i truly want for 2019 is to be healthy and for my loved 1’s to be healthy & happy.
⚪️
⚪️
⚪️
this year included a lot of first:
* we celebrated our first chinese new year in shanghai.
* we took grace to her first concert in shanghai. it was all of our 1st times  seeing john legend.
* we saw pandas at the chengdu sanctuary and had pizza that was so close to home. pandas are 1 of my favorite animals.
*  we went to the great wall of china in beijing. * i did my first interview for raising grace.
* we spent a short but sweet time in kazakhstan and russia.
* we went to paris with my parents and it was my 1st time at disneyland along with grace. * we went to wuqing for the 1st time.
* we went to thailand for grace’s bday again.
* we went to shanghai for the global games party.
* we went to a uyghur wedding and had so much fun.
* i shared my #metoo experience * we made an amazing thanksgiving dinner in our hotel room.
* we had a great christmas in our hotel room. though we were suppose to be away. it worked out perfect.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
"가장 곤란한 것은 모든 사람들이 생각하지 않고 나오는 대로 말하는 것이다. _ 알랭(alain, 프랑스 철학자)"
.
 2019년.
.
서로가 서로에게 상처주지 않고 그러므로 누구도 상처 입지 않는 시간이 되길 바랍니다. .

내가 하는 말이 상대방의 가슴에 상대방의 삶에 어떤 영향을 미칠지 한 번이라도 생각하고 이야길 한다면, 험한 세상 속에 서로가 말을 전하고 살 정도로 가까이에 있는 이들끼리 버팀이 되지는 못할지언정, 상처를 주고받으며 마음에 병이 들어 세상을 회피하는 불행은 더 이상 일어나지 않을지 모릅니다. .
.
말하기 전에 그저 단 한 번만 생각해봐주세요. 
내 말이 그에게 상처를 주지는 않을까.
내가 하는 말이 과연 저들에게 어떤 영향을 미칠까. 
내가 하는 행동이 과연 어떤 결과를 불러올 것인가. .
.
어릴 적 읽었던 명심보감에 나오던 말인데요, 
지금까지도 잊지 않고 절대적으로 믿으며 살아가는 말이 하나 있습니다. 이 말은 제가 악해지거나 분노가 치미는 순간, 복수심에 불타거나 뿌리치기 힘든 유혹에 당면했을 때 늘 저를 잡아주어 그저 꾹 참고 제가 가야만 하는 제 삶의 길에서 벗어나지 않도록 해 준 말이지요.
.
. "種瓜得瓜요 種豆得豆니 天网恢恢 하여도 疎而不漏 이니라."
"종과득과요, 종두득두니 천망회회 하여도 소이불루 이니라." 즉, "오이를 심으면 오이를 얻을 것이고 콩을 심으면 콩을 얻을 것이니, 하늘의 그물이 성긴 것 같아도 결코 빠트리는 일이 없다." .
.
2019년엔 부디 서로서로 배려하고 위하며 
함께 일하고 함께 나누고 함께 살아가는 따뜻한 시간이길 바라봅니다. .
.
지난 한 해 모두들 고생 많으셨습니다. 
새해 복 많이 받으세요.
.

text:
🥂2018, vilket år🥂

under året som gått har våga växt så otroligt mycket. vi har deltagit i event, på konserter, festivaler, konferenser. vi har träffat många otroliga och fantastiska människor som stöttar oss, och vill hjälpa oss att kämpa tillsammans för ett nöjesliv fritt från sexuella trakasserier. här är några highlights: 
januari: våga deltar i ett #metoo prehack där vi träffar många fina eldsjälar. de lila ballongerna är såklart med!💜✨ februari: våga skickade ut en enkät, som sedan har varit en viktig grund till vår utbildning riktad till arrangörer och vaktbolag. tack alla som delat med sig. era röster är sjukt viktiga 💜✨ mars: på vågas instagram dyker det första helghyfset upp, "var inte påstridig på dansgolvet".💜✨ april: i lokaltidningen i helsingborg pryder vågas team förstasidan. texten berättar om vågas satsning i staden i samarbete med #visionsfonden. 💜✨ maj: våga taggar #dunkadunkers2018 💜✨ juni: på social impact day minglar våga med inspirerande människor. 💜✨ juli: taggen inför #statementfestival börjar trappas upp. våga berättar på sin instagram att några från teamet självklart kommer vara på festivalen💜✨ augusti: våga arbetar med #hxfestivalen 💃🏻. på plats utbildar vi personalen i hur sexuella trakasserier kan hanteras och förebyggas. här vill våga tacka #visionsfonden som gjorde arbetet möjligt. 💜✨ september: våga utbildar värdarna för ngbgfestivalen. denna gatufest i malmö gick av stapeln med 0 rapporterade brott. 💜✨ oktober: under oktober skickade våga ut en enkät som blivit början för projektet #helsingborgvågar. resultatet från projektet kommer inom kort.💜✨ november: @battre.an.de.flesta skriver i sitt nyhetsbrev om vågas arbete ✨💜. december: våga får möjligheten att släppa fantastisk merch med hjälp av @musikkaofficial . dessutom auktioneras en av tröjorna ut i @välkommenhemtillmalmos livestream i samband med #musikhjälpen2018 💜✨ våga vill tacka 2018 för alla minnen. framför allt vill vi tacka er, fina underbara följare som står med oss, peppar oss - och visar att vi är många som vill skapa förändring. ikväll dansar vi in 2019 💃🏻💃🏻. #våga #vagatillsammans #2018 #2019 #sverige #minnen

— sue echelmeyer.

text:
[werbung / rezensionsexemplar]
gerade eben habe ich meine rezension zu "the future is female - was frauen über feminismus denken" auf meinem blog (link in der beschreibung) veröffentlicht. es würde mich freuen wenn ihr vorbeischauen würdet. mir hat das buch wahnsinnig gut gefallen. vielen dank auch nochmal an den @goldmann_verlag für das rezensionsexemplar. ❤
.
inhalt:
die welt, in der frauen heute leben, ist trotz #metoo und immer größer werdenden öffentlichen protesten gegen die geschlechterungleichheit noch immer massiv vom gender pay gap, der sehnsucht nach dem perfekten bikinibody und mansplaining definiert. »the future is female! was frauen über feminismus denken« ist das buch für mädchen und frauen, die sich mit diesem ungenießbaren cocktail nicht länger zufriedengeben wollen, eine einzigartige und vielstimmige textsammlung. frauen von der hollywood-ikone bis zur teenie-aktivistin erzählen darin ihre ganz persönliche geschichte; alle geschichten zusammengenommen entwickeln eine kraft, die die alte welt aus den angeln heben kann und dem f-wort einen ganz neuen glanz verleiht. der feminismus von heute definiert sich über das dafür und miteinander und nicht ewig gestrig über das dagegen, er ist eine unwiderstehliche notwendigkeit – und jede einzelne von uns gehört dazu!.
.
.

text:
sokakta bu hareket ceza nedeni!
#
haber merkezi̇ - kadınlara yönelik cinsel şiddet önemli bir toplumsal mesele olarak üzerinde tartışılmaya devam edilirken sokakta yürüyen kadına asılma, ıslık çalma, laf atma gibi eylemleri de suç kapsamına alan ülkelerin sayısı artıyor. #metoo hareketiyle birlikte bazı ülkeler kadınlara yönelik taciz kapsamına girebilecek eylemlere daha sert cezalar getiriyor. en son fransa'da yürürlüğe giren yasa ile yolda kadınlara veya erkeklere ıslık çalınması da taciz kapsamına alındı. söz konusu yasa tacizciye 90 euro'dan başlayan cezalar öngörüyor. sokakta tacize para ve hapis cezaları getiren ülkeler bu yasal uygulamaların sokakta özellikle kadınların maruz kaldığı davranışlara karşı caydırıcı etkide bulunmasını umuyor. fransa ile birlikte 5 ülkede daha yolda yürüyen kadına ıslık çalmak sözlü tacize giriyor ve bu eylemler için söz konusu ülkelerin yasalarında somut cezalar öngörülüyor.

text:
domestic violence survivors can face ongoing and challenging effects after enduring physical, mental, and emotional abuse. it can take time for a survivor to adjust to living in a safe environment, especially if a perpetrator was severely violent and/or committed the actions over an extended period of time.
while addressing this pain can be overwhelming, the healing process can help survivors develop inner strengths and lessen their fear of safety for themselves and their families. on the journey to recovery, survivors and those who support them should understand that healing takes time. the effects of this trauma can vary widely person to person due to individuals’ responses to stress, age, and the frequency and severity of abuse.
.

tweet_full:
domestic violence survivors can face ongoing and challenging effects after enduring physical, mental, and emotional abuse. it can take time for a survivor to adjust to living in a safe environment, especially if a perpetrator was severely violent and/or committed the actions over an extended period of time.
while addressing this pain can be overwhelming, the healing process can help survivors develop inner strengths and lessen their fear of safety for themselves and their families. on the journey to recovery, survivors and those who support them should understand that healing takes time. the effects of this trauma can vary widely person to person due to individuals’ responses to stress, age, and the frequency and severity of abuse.

mgtow 101: depreciating assets
👂
👂
these bentleys once had a value of a quarter million dollars before they left the lot. now they are cheaper than some mercedes, audis and bmw's. i know people who have purchased bentleys for under 40k only to find out a simple repair can cost between 10k-50k. no matter how cheap you buy it, it isn't wise to spend on a depreciating value with high maintenance fees.
👂
👂
i would not call myself the most erudite investor, but there is one thing i am absolutely certain of, no matter how incredibly hot a woman is — from the moment you lay eyes on her — she is a depreciating asset. if someone told you that, if you put half your life savings in a mutual fund that was absolutely guaranteed to return negative results, no matter how hard you invested, would you put even a dime in to it? the same must be said for women. the only safe bet is to rent not buy. and even when renting, better be sure not to do anything that will “extend the lease” indefinitely — such as knock her up or marry her. have your fun and move on.
👂
👂

text:
it's not the waking it's the rising. 
every small word, deed or action of resistance against this system, helps, echos, reaches others. is a light.

it can be defeated. we can end patriarchy & rape culture & the oppression of so many.

to survivors.. i hope you heal & find comfort in feminism, therapy, friendship. i'm not sure closure is possible, it's definitely a journey, but there is solidarity & support & if you have to write it on your bedroom mirror - it was not your fault. be gentle & kind to yourself as you would a friend. i know you are strong, but it's ok to be vulnerable too. x

to people who care.. listen. believe survivors, trust them, respect them. there is no humanity in the justice system no room for the emotional & rape or assault are highly emotive topics. people are allowed to deal with their experience in their own way. there is no 'wrong' or 'right'. where possible attend marches, sign petitions, show support, be an ally. speak out when you can, whether sharing a link or challenging a friend on a comment at a party or in the office.

if you are safe & in a position to do so, where you do not fear for your safety.. & you feel able to do so.. please try & challenge people on problematic comments, language or action. "if you are neutral in situations of injustice, you have chosen the side of the oppressor" (i have no problem with people not feeling able to speak out if they feel vulnerable, psychologically, unwell, or in a potentially unsafe situation - but i feel privileged allys - usually straight white men, rarely have an excuse for their silence in the face of injustice apart from not wanting to upset the apple cart, or challenge a friend which is so cowardly & normalises the language & actions that encourage entitlement & disrespect that leads to assault & rape to continue). #metoo #feminism #endrapeculture #consent #respect #ibelieveher #letboyscry #endgenderstereotypes #endviolence #boyswillbeheldaccountablefortheiractions #standwithsurvivors #rise #solidarity

text: este año, miles de personas alrededor del mundo levantaron sus voces para decir basta a la violencia y discriminación en contra de las mujeres. su mayor visibilización fue a través de campañas como #niunamenos, en américa latina y #metoo, en hollywood. en nuestro país, fueron las estudiantes universitarias las que empoderaron y crearon el movimiento feminista, a través de exigencias como una educación no sexista, fin del patriarcado y tolerancia cero frente al acoso y abuso sexual en las instituciones de educación superior. por ahora, lucen a su favor la institucionalización de protocolos de actuación frente casos de acoso en 23 universidades y la creación de comisiones de género en distintos planteles. ¿qué viene ahora? el 8 de marzo, día en que se conmemora mundialmente a la mujer, se apunta la primera marcha del año para reinstalar el protagonismo en favor de la oficialización de las soluciones a sus demandas. “va a ser una huelga con protagonismo en las mujeres, pero que llamará al conjunto de la sociedad a movilizarse por reivindicaciones que transformen radicalmente las vidas precarizadas que tenemos hoy en este país”, adelanta a la tercera la vocera de la ong coordinadora feminista 8 de marzo, alondra carrillo. la ola feminista: lo que dejó y lo que proyecta para el 2019 en latercera.com. revisa nuestro sitio

⠀
от всей души поздравляю вас с наступающим новым 2019 годом!🌲🌲🌲🌲
⠀
желаю всем быть любимыми и любить, ❤ красивыми, быть всегда в отличном настроении, финансовой свободы,💸 мира и добра в ваших семьях!
⠀

хочу подвести итоги уходящего 2018 года:
⠀

1.благодаря инстаграму я нашла себе надежных друзей!
⠀

2. начала развиваться как личность , прокачиваю себя в соц.сетях, но главное мое открытие-это то, что я познакомилась с компаниией gmmg в которой успешно развиваюсь, и уже есть хорошие денежные результаты💸

text:
2018 is drawing to a close, and it is time for us to look back on the past year and what we’ve achieved in it. our team grew from three full time members to four full time members, while our hindi editor stayed on as a part time member. our team now includes japleen pasricha – founder-director, asmita ghosh – campaign manager, swati singh – hindi editor, amudha mv – content editor and suman saurav – digital editor. we also shifted offices this year to take up a small space in a building in naraina vihar, new delhi.

with our little team growing in size slowly but surely, so is the impact of our work. our average monthly website hits doubled, and our social media following rose as well! our writer family grew by over a 100 people, and we also had the distinct pleasure of significantly increasing the number of writers from marginalized positions, making our content more reflective of diverse sociopolitical identities.

we ran several successful campaigns this year, both in-house and in partnership with organizations whose work we admired. in-house campaigns drew on our followers’ experiences and amplified them, while partnered campaigns boosted valuable work that social good organizations had been doing. in #chalkfullbullying, we highlighted stories of gender-based bullying in schools, while in #unsanskarilove, we spotlighted unconventional love stories and how difficult it is for queer, inter-caste or inter-faith love to survive in india. 
our #didyouask campaign anticipated the second wave of the #metoo movement, in which we used thought provoking videos created by pld india to spark a conversation on navigating consent and handling rejection. our instagram stories saw many deeply personal incidents being, where followers resonated with the snippets in the video and added their own thoughts to it, leading to a highly enriching conversation. the #unstereotypecinema campaign in partnership with oxfam india was also a major conversation starter, where we unpacked the patriarchal biases in our favourite indian films and spoke about how cinema systematically objectifies and dehumanizes women.

read more. link in bio.

text:
these are the friends you pray for. 
the ones who show up. 
the ones who are there, for every milestone, every dark moment; 
when you’re in a pile of tissues + self-doubt. the ones who love you + see you just as clearly when you’re dark and when you’re light. .
.
the ones who are there to laugh with you at the batshit insanity that is mama life. 
the ones who show up at your house with alcohol-free beverages, and ask if it’s ok that they drink in front of you. 
the ones that show up at the hospital to welcome your babies.
who bring you food + mala bracelets when you’re drowning, and bring you to all your favorites place for your birthday because they just know.
the ones who cry harder than you when you sell your home and move to a new town. .
.
the ones who remind you who you truly are, for those moments when you simply can’t remember. .
.
these people are your north star 🌟 always leading you back home. and i thank god everyday for their  pure love in my life. it’s a gift from god.
.
.
.
who are your north stars? tag them here + celebrate your connection✨

text:
#bestnine2018 
1. 이번년도 현장 5개 뛰었다! 많이 배웠고 너무 즐거운 (힘들었지만...) 날들이였습니다 내년에는 더 능숙한 스태프가 될게요...! (제 현장에도 와주세요... 언제일지 모르지만)
2. #metoo 는 끝나지 않는다
3. 진짜 어느때보다 행복했던 생일! 축하해주신 분들 다 너무 감사드리고 서프라이즈 파티해준 돌포놈들 은혜갚겠습니다 (^^)
4•5. 전국노동자대회
6. 부국제 갔을때 의정신희운하 <💕 뽀쟉이 내동기들 
7. 좆망한 시간표 > 성적도 비슷하게 나옴
8. 부국제에서 산 모자인데 노랑머리라서 잘 어울렸나보다.. 검정하니까 안어울림
9. ?? 박철우랑 현장가서 밖에 쭈굴탱하는건데 이거 왜 베스트 나인이지 ?ㅁ?

1년 너무 길었다 ~ 쓰레기같이 살았지만 나름 남은건 많지 뭐 내년에는 조금 더 건강한 삶을 살겠어요 🙂

text: i started my year as a feminist in residence @projectforemptyspace and debuted lnteriors: we are all pink inside (and am so happy that 2019 will start with a group show that includes the installation) and am so grateful to @rjampol and @browngirlcurator - i had so many great moments @projectforemptyspace this year. (that’s where i got the “fuck you pay me” shirt! ) i’m still in remission! that’s a big yay and wow and grateful to be alive and have a little family with @mckenziewark3000 . i published a few things- about @catalinacruzny and @ifpfilm - ifp was a huge part of my 2018 and surprised it didn’t show up here, their support for my film project is huge. my high school started to face it’s reckoning about abuses. i taught what is rape culture? , the body in performance art, and rape culture and sexual justice. i painted dicks. i danced. lots of failures too- still have done that last edit on my book project, i haven’t been able to write to my school to ask for what i want them to do, i got rejected from many, many grants and a big institutional thing that i really thought was going to happen, didn’t. i’ve been slow to process some emotions, and got really fucked up by the kavanaugh hearings. i’m still working on my internal white supremacy and internalized patriarchy. i still want to “win” even though i know there’s no winning. i’ve found hope in this shitshow. friends were surprised i wasn’t more vocal about #metoo and i haven’t been in touch with my family in canada and buffalo much. i’m still healing, but finally feeling much stronger. here’s to love and creativity and tenderness and vulnerabily in 2019. also, why was there no option to save the mother in bandersnatch?

text:
walking into the new year with my best girlfriend — my daughter. 
this has been an important year for many women around the world. whatever criticisms #metoo movement deserves, it also helped many women (and men) to speak up, to process their trauma and to feel more entitled to not be subjected to abuse and exploitation. raising a young girl, becoming aware of and healing my own traumas, all have been aided by this big debate. yes, papers try to turn everything into the usual money-making media circus, but personally i found a lot of reassurance and support from what was happening on a global scale. finding one’s own sacred physical emotional mental and spiritual integrity that shouldn’t be interfered with or compromised in work and other circumstances and teaching the same to my daughter — this is one of the biggest themes of 2018 for me. 
the other side of the coin, of confronting those who don’t respect the physical or psychological boundaries of other humans, is how we project ourselves to the world. in everyday life and on social media. sex sells, but if we really care about ourselves and our children and want to be part of the bigger wave of change that’s happening in global consciousness, we have to confront ourselves and reflect on how we are contributing to this issue with our own behavior. i‘ve been trapped in a narcissistic selfie culture of social media for at least one year and a half it was enough to realize how toxic and damaging it is to one’s soul. while i love seeing photographs of people i follow here, there’s a fine line between sharing your being and energy on an occasional basis or a daily obsession of trying to sell yourself through never-ending stream of selfies. i cannot comment on fashion industry that basically is based on sexualized images, but to see intelligent women, writers, poets, artist, actors, yogis who project themselves like cheap models and seem to be totally lost in their own narcissistic ego is painful. let’s not encourage it here, let’s speak up against it & help each other overcome this disease of the soul. this is our responsibility in the #metoo movement: to re-write the rules of the game that belongs to the past.
name: Vera Graziadei

walking into the new year with my best girlfriend — my daughter. 
this has been an important year for many women around the world. whatever criticisms #metoo movement deserves, it also helped many women (and men) to speak up, to process their trauma and to feel more entitled to not be subjected to abuse and exploitation. raising a young girl, becoming aware of and healing my own traumas, all have been aided by this big debate. yes, papers try to turn everything into the usual money-making media circus, but personally i found a lot of reassurance and support from what was happening on a global scale. finding one’s own sacred physical emotional mental and spiritual integrity that shouldn’t be interfered with or compromised in work and other circumstances and teaching the same to my daughter — this is one of the biggest themes of 2018 for me. 
the other side of the coin, of confronting those who don’t respect the physical or psychological boundaries of other humans, is how we project ourselves to the world. in everyday life and on social media. sex sells, but if we really care about ourselves and our children and want to be part of the bigger wave of change that’s happening in global consciousness, we have to confront ourselves and reflect on how we are contributing to this issue with our own behavior. i‘ve been trapped in a narcissistic selfie culture of social media for at least one year and a half it was enough to realize how toxic and damaging it is to one’s soul. while i love seeing photographs of people i follow here, there’s a fine line between sharing your being and energy on an occasional basis or a daily obsession of trying to sell yourself through never-ending stream of selfies. i cannot comment on fashion industry that basically is based on sexualized images, but to see intelligent women, writers, poets, artist, actors, yogis who project themselves like cheap models and seem to be totally lost in their own narcissistic ego is painful. let’s not encourage it here, let’s speak up against it & help each other overcome this disease of the soul. this is our responsibility in the #metoo movement: to re-write the rules of the game that belongs to the past.

text:
31 dicembre, quasi 2019.

stamattina ho visto l’ultima alba dell’anno. era arancione e sembrava così lontana da essere irragiungibile.

2018.

l’anno della voce delle donne, l’anno delle cose possibili, l’anno del gerundio.

non è solo il #metoo che ha scoperchiato il vaso di pandora. sono stati 365 giorni di una coscienza nuova, libera, sdoganata. senza freni, senza tabù, controidicazioni. marce e parole urlate o scritte su cartelli immensi, hanno fatto seguire (finalmente) delle azioni. ci siamo abbracciate in due parole e un hasthag e, probabilmente sentite meno sole. probabilmente anche più forti. coraggiose lo eravamo già.

le cose possibili.

ci vuole solo coraggio, in fondo, per avere il mondo. (perché stanno inventando i robot che un giorno sostituiranno gli umani). il mondo è in una vita che ha coraggio e cambia il suo corso dopo un viaggio in thailandia di due settimane, il mondo è in una 29enne del bronx che arriva al congresso, il mondo è anche dei muri che vengono costruiti e che ci impongono di ripensare alle barriere, ai limiti, alle lacerazioni. il mondo è di chi è sulla copertina del time, di chi inventa un’ app, una soluzione, un’innovazione e entra nella classifica di forbes. il mondo è di chi va al cinema il mercoledì e prende un treno tutti i giorni per arrivare a destinazione.

il gerundio.

michelle obama ha appena lanciato il suo nuovo libro, si chiama “becoming”, letteralmente “diventando”. mi piace il gerundio perché è un tempo in itinere. non si è ancora compiuto. si sta compiendo. mentro lo vivi. mentre lo decidi. mentre non lo sai. mentre, poi, lo scopri. chi vuoi diventare, dove vuoi andare, dove vuoi amare.

la ciclicità di questi 365 giorni è stata velocissima. a maggior ragione se non si passa più dalle mezze stagioni.

le albe invernali in un attimo sono già quelle estive. “un altro anno che finisce e mi spaventano questi sospiri in cui si trasforma il tempo”. se qualcuno mi chiedesse (non è ancora successo, perciò questa conversazione con il foglio bianco) una sola cosa per il nuovo anno, risponderei che voglio il gerundio. "becoming". #2018

text:
wow. what a year. so many highs and plenty of lows. this year i built relationships with family members i'd never even met. my dad, my grandmother, aunties, uncles, cousins... people who i will cherish and love dearly for the rest of my life. i spent 8 hard weeks training for my first mma fight and won with pride. i was broke at times. some days i didn't even want to be here. i was homeless and then housed all in the space of 3-4 months. i lost people. whether they passed away, went to jail or even just disappeared. i've watched long term friends grab life by the horns and break down barriers against all odds. i've seen others crumble under the weight of every day life. i sat in court every day for a week to eventually watch a man get sent down for the destruction he inflicted upon people i love, and then i watched those loved ones triumph in piecing themselves back together. my friends have inspired me to do and be better, not just after the clock strikes twelve but always. every day. in the new year i'll be granted with some funding for my music and words can't describe how excited i am to get the ball rolling again. i'm proud of my family and how far we've come. i'm proud of all my friends who overcame addiction and who spoke out about mental health. all my sisters who spoke out when the #metoo hashtag came into play, i'm proud of you for your strength and honesty. and so i'd like to wish each and every one of you a happy new year. thank you for supporting me. thank you for believing in what i do and thank you for getting this far into my essay without falling asleep.

lest be said, this year has been a bloody whirlwind. but none of my achievements would be at all credible if i didn't have my stunning fiancé by my side through it all. so this year my darling, is to you. to us. we deserve all the fun and joy 2019 brings and more. my life partner. i love you kiddo ❤️

#entrepreneurship is not a road i planned on paving in 2018, but i am so happy that i did and i am excited to continue it into 2019.

i preach and teach #consent and #kindness and i love the #journey it has taken me on!

for anyone in the business and #entrepreneurlife i highly recommend the @dailygreatness
planners and journals! they have everything you know you need and everything you haven't thought of, jam packed inside.

see you all in 2019!

remember tonight: "consent is everything" & no one is consenting to being on the road with drunk drivers. so please call an uber, a friend or hop on transit.

text: 2018 has brought with it a lot of change- some i was ready for and some that was thrust upon me (#metoo). 2018 was my last year in nyc but it was also my first red carpet in la. 2018 brought with it my first time directing, my first time buying a car, and my first time being in a wedding. i spent far too much time in 2018 dealing with drunk idiots, pouring foamy beer, and building upon my overall distaste for the general public. but i also spent much of 2018 surrounded by some incredibly funny human beings that made those days & nights worth it. and while 2018 didn’t bring me many auditions, i started my career as a content creator. i said hello to new hair and goodbye to my sweet girl lily. 2018 didn’t feel like a remarkable year to me until i went back to do this #2018in12photos. and then i saw all the wondrous adventures i have been fortunate for this year. thank you to this year for teaching me what my definition of success truly is. thank you 2018 for revealing to me my shadow and for giving me a chance to find the courage to journey within that cave. i look forward- always - to every moment i am lucky enough to call myself alive. see you in la, 2019! ✌🏻🌞

text:
2018 was a year of ups and downs but it was definitely a year of history-making moments for women all around the world. here are just few things we accomplished:
1️⃣women broke records in elections all over the world from the record number of female candidates elected to the u.s house of representatives to spain's female-majority cabinet even here in lebanon where we saw a record number of women on the ballot. an unprecedented 113 women registered as candidates, and 86 of them made it to candidate lists. this was a whopping increase from 2009, when only 12 women candidates had registered.
2️⃣in saudi arabia, women were finally given the legal right to drive
3️⃣the usa gymnastics team found their voices and stood up to their abuser.
4️⃣movies with strong female leads ruled the box office.
5️⃣nadia murad, a yazidi woman who was captured by isis, won the nobel peace prize
6️⃣film producer harvey weinstein arrives at manhattan criminal court in new york. weinstein was one of the first men accused of sexual misconduct in the #metoo movement
7️⃣christine blasey ford, a california college professor, accused then-supreme court nominee brett kavanaugh of sexual assaulting her in high school 
8️⃣britain’s prince harry  broke the british rules by marrying american actress meghan markle.
9️⃣"he's never taken a game from a man because they said 'thief.' for me it blows my mind. but i'm going to continue to fight for women" -serena williams at the us open
🔟participants march against sexual assault and harassment at the #metoo march in the hollywood section of los angeles
name: Club Féministe du LAK

text:
2018 brought on a collective shift in consciousness. it also revealed the illusion of separation in heartbreaking ways. the duality of right + wrong and left + right are designed to keep us down. 
𖥳
this was very apparent with the #metoo movement and rising of the feminist movement, which i have been a part of. here’s the thing- when it’s not done in balance, it’s actually a masculine approach to bringing down the patriarchy. the #divinefeminine is truly rising when it honors the #divinemasculine. when there is man bashing and hate of any kind, it’s only creating more separation.  when we create space for men to get in touch with their emotions and express them, we are healing. 
𖥳
as someone who came forward and told my truth about (some) of the sexual abuse i’ve experienced, i have to say that the most healing part of my journey was forgiving the men who acted out of their suffering when they abused me.  forgiveness released all the shame i was carrying around unknowingly. 
𖥳
forgiveness creates compassion. my intent in 2019 is to take aligned, compassionate action to continue shifting the collective out of the illusion of separation. it’s incredible how many people are waking up right now. 2018 showed me that it’s possible to bring balance back on earth. 
𖥳
my wish for 2019 is for everyone to experience our true nature of oneness, of divine love, of whatever name you call it. much love and all the light. 💗kat 
𖥳
📸 @root_for_food

text: 2018 - blessed, happy, powerful and free. passion, love, luck and joy. best time of my life. fell in love with canada and built a new home there. the start of a new, exciting chapter. intersectional feminist empowerment. sisters raising together and supporting each other #metoo #niunamas. losing hope and regaining it every other day, quite a weird feeling but it balanced out in the end. new lessons learned and old, wrong lessons forgotten. lots of good books. played my fav jams 24/7 and counting. discovered country music and whisky. a lot of hip hop too. quality memes brought to you by millennials and gen z. yummy food as often as needed, special thanks go to chocolate, cookies, sushi and padthai. congrats, vegan food! you kinda changed my ways. pizza didn't make it to the list this year, but it's still part of my soul. poutine, you were up there. new perspectives and philosophies. amazing buds and pals. finally visited la and vancouver. many mind blowing parties and after parties. lots of cool people i got to know and miss. moments that will be forever treasured. a shit ton of knowledge about sustainability and social and environmental responsibility. mental health awareness. self-love, self-care, body positivity, gym and pampering days. setting new goals and fighting for them. let's wrap up this pretty dope year. 2018, you did better than good. 2019, you're on! show me what you got ❤ cheers 🍻

text:
happy new year! - for me i’ll be the big 51 in one week. for the new year and a more “authentic” me (hate that word but using it anyhow) i’ve gone back to my natural color red. well, auburn is more like it but i’m working it a little brighter this time around after being blonde for the past 25 years. i’ve had several people tell me they don’t like it, which is funny because i never asked their opinion and don’t care. you would think some would know me by now or at least get my “i don’t give a💩” vibe. 😝 to all who walk the path less paved, don’t listen to anyone but the voice inside your soul. don’t allow any outer negativity to cause you to be afraid of who you are or second guess what you know to be true in your heart. don’t be afraid to stand out and stand up for what you believe in. and ladies, speak kindly of others, stay away from drama and rumors and only speak the truth. in this day and age i’m seeing and hearing a lot of negativity towards each other and men and this is the time to use #girlpower and the #metoo movement with kindness, care and responsibility. not as a means of retribution and control. .
.
.
#loveandlightthrough2019 #sparkle #newyear #newyear2019 #findyoursparkle #beyourself #gonered #neversecondguessyourself #womenstandup #womenstandstrong #together
name: Tracy Germaine

text:
happy new year everyone! this was my 2018. going through these, i'd forgotten that half of the stuff happened just this year!! it has been an adventurous year of travel both for business and pleasure to massachusetts, orlando, and salt lake city. 
i got to walk with the @womensmarchnyc expressing the love i have for my country.
i got to see so many of my loved ones perform, friends get married, and new films be produced.
it's been a magical potter filled year with some of the most incredible friends. i saw @hpplayus twice and got to meet some of the cast, went to @nyhistory and got to see jkr's original sketches and plans of the potter books, finally went to @comicconnyc, saw an early premiere of @crimesofgrindelwald, and went to @harrypotteruniversal! 
and at the start of this year, my first short @innocencefilm2017  premiered at @iffnyfestival and won best short film and continued to win awards in excellence the rest of the year. (news on streaming release soon to come! 🎬) i am so beyond grateful for my experiences of this year. putting it all together reminds me to not sweat the small things and to love the adventure of life surrounded by my loved ones. on to 2019! 
#happynewyear #newbeginnings #lastyear #thisyear #harrypotter #universalorlando #hogwarts #afternoontea #womensmarch #bestshortfilm #womeninfilm #femaleproducer #awardwinning #crimesofgrindelwald #cursedchild #broadway #theater #travel #hamilton #actress #actor #screenwriter #femalefilmmaker #femalefilmmakerfriday #potterheadforever #metoo

text:
“live as if you were to die tomorrow. learn as if you were to live forever.” - mahatma gandhi

before thinking about your new year resolutions, reflect on your past. what are the things that you accomplished in 2018? write down everything that comes to mind, big or small.  don’t overthink it and just let it flow. you’ll be surprised at how many accomplishments you have, even despite some hardships. really take in your accomplishments as you’re writing them and feel that sense of pride.  each accomplishment will build your confidence as we’re entering the new year. 
now what do you want to accomplish in 2019?  do your goals align with your greater purpose?  when you have clarity on your “why“ you will find it easier to be motivated every day to accomplish your goals.

once you have your purpose- aligned goals, write them down in detail and imagine yourself accomplishing these goals as if they’ve already happened.

don’t second-guess your goals comparing yourself to someone who may be further along. remember, these are your goals and not anyone else’s.

think of yourself as a blank canvas and each brush stroke is a goal moving towards your beautiful painting of your purpose.  don’t worry about the final artwork, just keep painting. 
and any rejection you might receive now, just turn it into fuel.  prove them wrong.  remember you are living your purpose and no one can stop you.

and if you temporarily fall off track you don’t need to wait until january 1st every year to start over. every day is the perfect day to get back on track or start something new!  you are unstoppable! 
i’m sending you love, good health and happiness for 2019!  happy new year! cheers! xo 
#youglowgirl

text:
yo yo everybody! happy new year! my name is kerilyn russo. you can find me at  @thisdreamergirl here on instagram.
.
the amazing @jenpastiloff invited me to takeover this account today, on my 44th birthday and well, can you tell i’m excited (maybe more nervous, let’s be real, i was shaking as i did this video.)
.
a little about me. i am a dreamer, a sensitive soul, a mama (honestly the best title i have at the moment) i am a believer of the teachings of a course in miracles - i have my own #metoo experience that i have never felt safe enough to share publicly, i know so many of you do too. i am a certified life coach, although currently that title doesn’t resonate.
.
i am a teacher and a student.
.
not one without the other.
.
i have been learning through experience about #codependency and #narcissism and i am now here here to remind you,
.
you are not alone.
.
just today, i have heard from three different women who have had to flee a scary situation and if you are reading this, please know,
.
you are strong.
you can be trusted.
.
you are not crazy. 
and again,
.
you are not alone. *you hear me?
.
so i have three more posts to share, and an offer at the end to work with me (learning to trust my inner #bossbabe ) i am giddy to share with you all i’m learning.
.
happy new year to you all who happen to stop scrolling on this video. away we go.
.
#randomtalkingvideo #thekerilynrussoshow #youarestrong #youarenotalone #trust #gaslighting #financialabuse

text:
women of color self-defense scholarship program now open
_____
the past couple years have been challenging for women, communities of color and lgbtq+ folks. recently we’ve seen increased incidents that may have undermined our sense of safety: attacks on immigrants and the lgbtq community, #metoo reports of epidemic sexual harassment and assault for women in all sectors, as well as a rise in intimate partner violence. safety continues to be a growing concern for many marginalized people. but we are also taking a stand and fighting back, helping each other, and in many cases triumphing as we did during the midterm elections with historic wins for women of color. 
_____
as jiu-jitsu martial artists, we are joining the fight by offering our knowledge to empower and strengthen our community. starting in 2019, sweaty betties and @fourelementsfitness will be joining forces to help end violence against women and girls, particularly among girls and women of color with low to modest means. we are collaborating to offer scholarships to a monthly women’s self-defense workshops. our goal is to provide free self-defense training for girls and women at four elements fitness in oakland, ca. 
____
sponsorship application for the february women’s self-defense workshop is open now and the deadline is jan.25. 2019. scholarships are first come, first served basis with limited amount per month. must be girls or women of color and ages 9+ to apply. no experience required to attend workshop. we reserve the right to close applications when full capacity are reached. if you or anyone you know are interested in a life-changing opportunity, please contact us at mollii@fourelementsfitness.com. workshop details below:
____
when: 
sat, feb 2, 2019
2-4pm

where:
@fourelementsfitness 
to apply/learn more:
woc.fourelementsfitness.com
_____
📷 by @molliik #womensselfdefense #selfdefense #beyourownbadass #empoweringwomen #empowerment #scholarships #scholarshipprogram #fightingback #metoo #timesup #nottoday #jiujitsuselfdefense #jiujitsu #community #strongcommunity #oakland #sweatybettiescommunity #fourelementsfitness #antibully #nottoday #unitedwearestrong #femalestrong #communityoutreach

text:
#24speciesofcrane project interim update

today the team was enjoying @kfc's all new vegan zinger burger with a side of that #veganbeef burrito from @tacobell yu quiero's and delicious orange julius's to slurp it all down. is it julius', juliuses, julius's, or juliusii?  anyways, we were amazing at the quality and flavor of organic vegan food that these big chains are able to produce and at >80% organic food, it's pretty good even for a stay at home vegan with convienient access market farms.

now that the scene has been set, a #shocking discovery was made recently by our research team. while examining crane feet, they noticed that while cranes feet are not webbed, ducks feet are. in addition to this newfoundland retrievers have webbed feet. this information totally blows the longstanding theory that crane dna was used in retrieving dogs to help them travel in wetlands, and points the finger a the duck. this makes sense as all of these purpose built killing machines are somehow magnetically drawn to ducks. this whole genetic modification thing knows no bounds. we now have factual evidence to suggest the whooping crane was forcibly bred with the dachshund to create the modern day grey hound, a bloody thirsty frankenstein of a dog that will chase a rabbit until they kill it.

it grosses us out when companies resort to #gmo and #breeding and worst of all selective reprodution to achieve increase farm efficiencies and better tasting healthier food. just look at the apple and corncob in the year 3000bc, pathetic really in size, and totally flavorless and hard, and now they are big juicy frankenfruits packed with vitamins we haven't even bothered to educate ourselves on because deep down we know that anything with omega 3 is fish, and we still love tomatoes but refuse to eat the flesh of another living being because we are all people.

so anyways, after a short break for the holiday period we will be back with the last remaining cranes just in time for hindu new years and some exciting news about life after the crane campaign. 
in the mean time, go #creaseforpeace

#origami @peta #notmypresident #trump2020 #cranesarepeople #lgbtqc #metoo #cranestoo #flatearth

text:
two years ago, we flew to memphis, tennessee, to spend a couple of days in "the south" during my winter break. 
it felt like a good idea at the time, especially since we had never spent new year's eve in the u.s. and the southern states promised to be a lot warmer than germany. but traveling in winter, as we learned -- and i should have remembered from a traumatic flight that involved a miniature prop plane, a snow storm, and a stranger whose fear of airplanes caused him to constantly clasp my thigh for moral support (#metoo, but also #propplanesaretheworst) --, follows its own rules. 
we got stuck in heathrow on the way to memphis (minneapolis and paris on the way back) and really struggled with the jetlag because of the delay. he then caught a man cold, i caught a legitimate cold, and both began to feel depressed because we had to do research on a story on emmett till (if you don't know, look it up, you'll understand). the fact that the presidential election had only happened two months ago didn't help either: some people were still visibly in shock, some people proudly donned their bumper stickers, but most people were just walking on eggshells. 
by new year's eve we were so exhausted that we sought shelter at a small but very cute thai restaurant in memphis. as we were the only customers, the elderly woman running the place buzzed with excitement and brought us plate after plate -- some of which we had ordered, some of which we had not but which, we thought, she wanted us to taste because, after all, this was new year's and maybe there were some good people left on this planet.

when the check arrived we not only had had the best mango sticky rice of our lives, but also one of the most expensive meals ever (and we have, by now, traveled to hawaii). we looked, incredulously, at the handwritten numbers on the bill, looked, incredulously, at each other, and then 
started laughing. 
was it overpriced? yes. 
was it worth it? yes. 
we payed, thanked her, drove to the hotel, went to bed at eight, and made the new year's resolution to never, ever again travel during this time of the year. 
happy new year. 
#travelgram #travelstories #memphis #happy2019

text: i’ve been battered and bruised both on the outside and the inside. let me tell you... the outside bruises fade and go away but the ones on the inside...those stick around! people keep telling me that you have to love yourself first before anything else in life will work out. i always ignored that saying and thought, “if one more person tells me that....” but, finally i have realized that they are right. without higher self-esteem and confidence, nobody stands a chance in your life/relationships. as the quote says, “tomorrow is the first blank page of a 365 page book”. you are the author of that book. only you ❤️ it’s an empty slate. what you choose to write in it is completely up to you! be good to yourself and make it the best 365 pages ever!!! i am going to start checking in on this page each day and try to motivate and inspire those like me that need it and maybe some who are motivated and just seem to be having a bad day. some posts will be from the gym and some will be other topics. like all other things, follow me if you choose but only if it’s a choice you make. i will try@to give good information. doing the best i can, best to all, victoria 😘❤️ #inspirationalquotes #motivation #inspiration #love #friendship #relationships #yougotthis #loveyourself #beyou #metoo #fitnessmotivation #gym #instagood #strongmindstrongbody #doyourbest #newyear #dontquit #fitness #workingout #loveyourself #loveyourselffirst #gethealthy #keepitup #getfit #youarebetterthanthat #overcomingobstacles #overcomingdepression #doitforyou #believeinyourself #believe

text:
2019 corker predictions 💫 .

what changes do you think 2019 will bring? these are our top 10! 🚀 .

1. clean meat in grocery store refrigerators 🧫 .

2. herbalism as preventative medicine 🌿 .

3. the end of single use plastics [plastic bags and straws be gone!]🥤 .

4. edibles in the office is the new happy hour 🌱 .

5. call centers convert to ai employees ☎️ .

6. climate change will either shut down or open up new businesses [ski hills suffer or extreme weather apparel thrives] 🌎🌚 .

7. women will get hired, heard + promoted as #metoo brought awareness in 2018 // 2019 is the year of change 💃🏽 .

8. the marriage of fitness and food [better fuel in gyms + studios] 🥑🤸🏽‍♀️ .

9. exercise for longevity + mental health > aesthetics [#doingthings matters] 🚴‍♀️ .

10. management skill required for all people managers: how to hire/train/retain remote workers/people you’ve never met in person 💡
