text:
hola muchis! el año 2018 acaba y se viene el 2019 con miles de desafíos más. para empezar este año quiero presentarme como la administradora de esta página. mi nombre es fary. me encanta viajar y leer sobre feminismo. cuando creé esta página fue porque estaba tan frustrada con tantos prejuicios hacia el feminismo que me dije: “yo puedo ayudar a mostrar a la gente, cual es el verdadero feminismo”. esta es mi versión de feminismo y escribo lo que realmente pienso. quiero que sepan que estas ganas de escribir y de hablar sobre el feminismo vienen desde lo más profundo de mis entrañas, pues yo me crié en guatemala. un bello país, pero que le hace falta un cambio de mentalidad. creo firmemente que muchos de nuestros problemas sociales se acabarían si tan solo la gente leyera un poquito sobre feminismo y lo aplicara en su vida. en fin, estan página está dedicada para l@s guatemaltec@s principalmente, porque es de donde conozco más. pero estoy segura que cualquier persona del mundo podrá identificarse con lo que aquí escribo. les deseo sororidad, amor propio, libertad y empoderamiento para este 2019. espero poder seguir escribiendo para ustedes. muchas gracias por seguirme y leer mis publicaciones!! 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼

2018 have been described as the year that women fought back. with the #metoo campaign, christine blasey ford standing up to brett kavanaugh and a record number of women voted into congress in the us, it really feels like the tide is slowly turning.
.
as we end the year, we normally turn to resolutions. the problem with resolutions? it re-enforces the idea that it is us that needs to change.
.
that we are wrong in some way.
.
we don’t need resolutions for 2019, we need revolutions!
.
my personal revolution? to support fat women’s rights to fertility support and equal care.
.
what is your revolution for 2019?

text:
as another year around the sun concludes, i find myself reflecting on my past 28 years and how i want to spend my final year before undeniable adulthood.  i want to let go of any shame i’ve been harboring about my past and be free to enter into a new year fresh.

four years ago, in the close of 2014,  i had my first experience with methamphetamine, and for the following year i experimented and abused the drug periodically (about 4 times in the course of the year). i lived so long in a deep depression and with heavy anxiety that i had stopped feeling all together, and crystal was a way to feel again.  so when i used, i used hard and carelessly.  i honestly didn’t care what happened to me, i just wanted to have fun.  these experiences were often accompanied with abusive men, a pair of which lead me to a week long hospital visit in rochester and some permanent damage physical and emotional damage. 
this year i celebrated 2 years completely free of crystal and it is wonderful.  i’ve learned to respect myself and those people who love me.  meth is scary & dangerous & selfish.  it gives you such a false perception of reality for so long that it becomes very hard (and depressing) to live outside that.

i think the worst thing to come out of this is the shame it has made me carry around for the last 2 years.  meth is dirty.  meth is gross.  society make it very clear what they think of people who do meth.  it felt like i was in the closet all over again.  i was so ashamed of myself that i just kept it bottled up and blamed myself over and over.  but blame doesn’t accomplish anything, taking responsibility does.  this year i took responsibility for my past, and i also forgave myself for fucking up. 
i have no regrets, i have learned so much about myself, the world, and this entire experience has brought me closer to discovering my path forward. 
thank you to those of you who have always been there for me, and continue to be.  and to anyone out there who’s struggling with anything, you’re not alone. -kevin reed 
#newyear #confession #metoo #drugabuse #substanceabuse #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #depression #instagay #gayguy #gayscruff #gayotter #instascruff #gay

text: 2018 i had to accept what i had been feeling for so long. it was those feelings that didn’t allow me to grow as a person, to be happy, to smile, to let go of the past. depression affected my life in so many ways. it claimed my cousins life, has taken a toll in my dad’s life and my son has been affected by it. i felt depression the most when i had to come to terms with being sexually molested as a child. i never healed. i have accepted certain labels, being a survivor, #metoo, having mental health issues. no i’m not crazy. i have survived a past that could have ended my life.  i am here. although, i tried to be strong for my children i couldn’t be and i wasn’t leading by example. i wanted them to believe in themselves, to be motivated, to have the strength in knowing that we can get past this. i failed to show them self love, acceptance, to believe in themselves. i have struggled with threats, control, and manipulation. to have ended a physically and mentally abusive relationship and to have to admit that my past has affected me to this day.  in the most humble way, i am asking you to share this post. without your help, our struggle will continue. i hope that one day soon i’ll be able to share another post where i can say that we are thriving and no longer just surviving. i have had to see my son be the most affected. i can’t let this continue. somehow we will get past this. thank you for everyone who i have met across this platform. i have read your posts, your words of encouragement. you are truly an inspiration. please keep our family in your prayers. god bless you and your family. please click the link in the bio. 🙏🏽

text:
2018 was awful.
.
there were a lot of good moments for me personally, but it feels disingenuous to say that the pain doesn’t matter because i’m fine in my cushy life. some of my privileges will protect me longer than others, but this nightmare still hits pretty close to home.
.

text:
2018 was 100 years since some women in the uk were given the vote. it was year of the me too and i weigh movements. it was the year where consent was a big topic, where predators including high profile ones finally were seen for what they are. where the wonderful people of ireland voted to legalise abortion; strengthening women’s rights over their own bodies. however, lets not forgot how far we have to go for those around us to understand consent, for the catcalling and up skirting photographs to stop and for meghan, duchess of sussex closing her own car door not to make front page news. 🤷‍♀️🤦‍♀️ equality has taken centre stage in 2018 and some small progress have been made, however it is up to all of us to make sure the conversations and progress continues. hope you all have a lovely new year. keep fighting and keep speaking out! 
#feminist #feminism #equality #happynewyear #2018 #2019 #newyear #metoo #iweigh #consent #votesforwomen #suffrage #suffrage100

31/12. siempre he pensado que este es el día más importante del año, pues en este dia siempre me tomó 5 minutos para mi. en primer lugar para dar gracias a dios por que siempre de su mano todo será posible, en esos 5 minutos también reflexiono y veo que todo lo que me pasa me deja una gran enseñanza. este año pude conocer a personas maravillosas tales como @nehomarabreu y @erv_vre ellos han marcado  un antes y un después en mi, son unos duros y como siempre  digo "gracias por tanto" a esa lista se le suman un sin fin de personas increíbles que pude conocer a lo largo de este 2018. si me preguntan por un logró sin duda alguna mencionara a @neosagency, pertenecer a esta gran familia no tiene precio. un lugar que se ha convertido en mi casa, mi lugar favorito. yo @luisalejandroof espero que este 2019 sea el año más fructífero de sus vidas. que cumplan todas y cada y se sus metas trazadas. un fuerte abrazo y próspero año nuevo🎊🎉📆ph:@aliriovargas

text:
the numeric significance of the calendar year is calculated by adding the digits of said year and reducing it to a single digit.
2+0+1+9= 12. 1+2=3. 
the universal number indicates the collective global vibration for that year, and gives us some insight of the energetic nature of our year to come. 
how you work with that vibration is dependent on you. 
for most, 2018 was a year of challenges and growth. you may have felt lost, confused, but excited. an inner fiery passion made itself known, even if you had no idea where or how to direct that passion. 
the divine feminine began to rise to make way for the union of the healed/balanced feminine and masculine.
the #metoo and #timesup movement were symbolic of the chaotic nature of the numeric "universal 2" year that was 2018. hollywood scandals, corporate greed, environmental distress, political drama..were all begining to be unveiled in their true light.
in 2019 we work with the 3 vibration (one of clarity, light, truth, also the number of ascended masters and the throat chakra) to communicate with our hearts and eachother to bring unity, clarity and a collectively beneficial vision of the future into fruition. 
universal year 3's are exciting ones, as they bring action, creativity, authenticity, compassion and truth to the forefront of our minds. 
if you've been feeling charged but undecided, lost, or confused, 2019 is a pivotal year of finding alignment and following our soul purpose. 
we will no longer be satisfied with living half-heartedly, but rather dive into the depths of our hearts and bring our desires to the forefront. 
universal year 3 is one of joy, communication, change, socializing, and living in pleasure. 
what does this mean for you? whatever you want it to mean. whether you shy away from this newfound energy and choose to live in the confining but familiar old paradigm is up to you. 
for me, i already feel a pull. a need to shed the old conditioning that led me to limit and constrict myself to be versions of myself that suited others. *continued in comments*

kevin spacey and harvey weinstein deny they have ever worked together. sources say, there was an extremely short-lived project that holds the record for fastest ‘green-lighting’ of any film in hollywood history. in less than 48 hours the project went from concept to lawyers preparing contracts. the film was a passion project of spacey’s, where he played a jazz musician that discovers hidden language among whales, learning of their ancient alien origin. spacey allegedly, took a meeting in weinstein’s hotel room and while discussing the film, coincidentally, they had both pulled their penises out, almost simultaneously. “there was definitely some synchronicity going on,” said spacey’s former assistant. the men had a big laugh before locking the deadbolt and spending the entire weekend fucking and snorting crystal meth. at some point during that drug-fueled sex marathon, the film was green-lit, only to be pulled from the official slate of weinstein projects in the following weeks. “i think both men felt a tinge of regret from their encounter with one another,” said an anonymous source.

text:
scriabin sonata 4 opus. 30, mvt 2 · prestissimo
—
mitrofan belaiev, outstanding patron of russian composers, scriabin’s publisher since 1894 and his stern, fatherly mentor in worldly matters, had died in december 1903. corresponding to this upheaval in personal life is a transformation in musical language, shown clearly in the sonata no 4, op 30 (1903). for this work scriabin wrote a programme: a poem describing flight to a distant star. it reflects the startling new philosophies he was imbibing:

thinly veiled in transparent cloud
a star shines softly, far and lonely.
how beautiful! the azure secret
of its radiance beckons, lulls me …
vehement desire, sensual, insane, sweet …
now! joyfully i fly upward toward you,
freely i take wing.
mad dance, godlike play …
i draw near in my longing …
drink you in, sea of light, you light of my own self …

these excerpts give a flavour of scriabin’s literary effusion, which hardly does justice to his music. it does, however, contain a number of motifs which recur in his mental world: light, colour, erotic desire, flight, dance, and the equation of the cosmos with the ego. the last-mentioned is close to the tat tvam asi—‘that art thou’—of sanskrit teaching, the universal oneness of mystic experience in many cultures; with a personality as self-absorbed as scriabin, however, it is possible to feel rather that he believes ‘all is myself!’—a rather different proposition.
·
happy new year's everyone!
.

.
.

text:
mgtow 101: do you know you? 
i see memes circulating like this all over social media, but most people don't really know themselves in relation to the world.

i was having a conversation with a homegirl, and she prompted me to do an experiment. i told her most people just want to he accepted and loved for who they are. part of that requires the spouse to actually know what you bring to the table.

i asked what makes you special?

what makes you standout from all the other women in the world?

she wrote a length 100 word response, and she was all wrong. so i told her from my lenses what separates you from others, and she immediately recognized why her own assessment of herself was wrong and shallow.

she named things that benefit other people and things that men love about her, but didn't name the things that benefits her self or the things that she should love about herself.

if you and your conscious were the only two people on planet what would they say about the other?

i would be willing to bet if i asked majority of men and women they would not know what truly separates them from others. if you don't know shit in this world you need to know yourself.

on the low, this is game for women too. women love to talk about themselves or hear you talk about them. so when you are talking to a woman study her and be able to tell her what makes her special, what separates her from every other person. don't use generic shallow bullshit but traits and skills that she truly possesses that require in depth thinking.

women want to be themselves and be seen for who they are. if they have to wear a mask to be around the guy, that guy won't be respected. they often say i shouldn't have to tell you how i feel, you're the man you supposed to know. the same applies to other areas, they feel they shouldn't need to wear masks you should be able to remove it and know who they are.

most couples are married to masks and the ones that aren't have a much better relationship. to wear a mask is to be enslaved. freedom is being exactly who you are, without having to hide anything especially from your wife or husband. this first requires knowing yourself and being honest about yourself.

text:
прорывом года названы техники отслеживания эмбрионального развития. ￼

science подвел итоги 2018 года © science magazine

журнал science составил список выдающихся научных достижений 2018 года. как сообщается на сайте издания, первое место в списке заняли техники, которые позволяют отслеживать и эмбриональное развитие на клеточном уровне. "еще со времен гиппократа биологи были ошеломлены загадкой того, как из единственной клетки развивается взрослое животное со множеством органов и миллиардами клеток… теперь же мы знаем, что процессы, с помощью которых клетки размножаются и "специализируются", зависят от днк", - говорится в статье.

открытием года, по версии составителей рейтинга, стали несколько техник, которые позволяют следить за "включением" определенных генов в клетках, что позволяет им выполнять определенные функции. "в результате мы получаем возможность отслеживать развитие организмов и органов в поражающих деталях, клетка за клеткой и с течением времени", - отмечают авторы рейтинга.

в список выдающихся открытий года попало также обнаружение останков девочки, которая была результатом скрещивания неандертальца и денисовского человека, одобрение первого препарата на основе рнк-интерференции и определение органики с эдиакарских окаменелостей белого моря.

отметили исследователи также обнаружение гигантского ударного кратера в гренландиии находку нейтрино, которые прилетели из далекой галактикой.

в качестве прорывов года было также отмечено и движение #metoo, которое позволило жертвам сексуальных домогательств в научной сфере говорить о них открыто.

читайте также: ученые объяснили вред сахара для здоровья

отметил журнал и провалы года. в этот список вошел скандал с рождением первых генетически модифицированных близнецов, ухудшение ситуации с глобальным потеплением и пожар в национальном музее бразилии, в результате которого были уничтожены многие ценные экспонаты.

text:
2018 was big. for all of us. we can’t remember a year in our lives that felt this intense in both positive and challenging ways. for us personally that’s meant becoming entrepreneurs, adding children, changing careers, building, pushing, building, running, and building! 💦⁣
⁣
in just over a year, countertop has: ⁣
gone from an idea, to a product bought all over the u.s. from our website and is now carried in stores from goop to whole foods⁣
been covered in elle, instyle, vogue, goop, cherry bombe and more (are we dreaming?)⁣
brought postpartum support to almost 1,000 new moms⁣
been embraced by nutritionists, health coaches, chefs, and most importantly, all of our amazing customers 😊️⁣
⁣
and along the way, it’s been women who have inspired us and for whom we are most grateful in 2018. ⁣
in particular: ⁣
🌟the women founders in food, beauty and wellness.⁣
🌟the women who have ushered in a new era of letting the light in with raw and public honesty around birth, motherhood, and our experiences as women.⁣
🌟the female led movements like #metoo and #normalizebreastfeeding ⁣
🌟the record numbers of women who stepped up, who ran for office, and who won. #changetheratio⁣
⁣
we look forward to sharing 2019 with you. our hope is that we support, care for, and embolden one another in every aspect of our lives. we are here to help support you and your families in your health and wellness, and are so grateful to enter this new year with you.⁣
⁣
love,⁣
jamie & nicole, lindsay & cori

text: art + activism = healing. this year, celebrating the 10th anniversary of my first record, disguised as fate, written when i was a traumatized teenage girl, was truly healing and cathartic. organizing on the artivism committee & marching with my girls, women, femmes & queers at the women’s march 2.0 was empowering and inspiring. remembering jessi zazu through music, organizing arts + activism workshops for youth, a memorial mural & being a part of @jessizazuinc has helped many of us channel grief, passion, and her spirit of creativity & justice. i’ve been introduced to an asian-american community of artists & activists, been featured on some cool podcasts & press, been proud to spread the good work of many organizations through my radio station @wxnafm somatic experiencing has begun to address the trauma in my body, and i am grateful for the #metoo & #timesup movements, making it easier for me to open up and fight against oppression & violence through bystander intervention trainings and grassroots collectives. these are just a few of the things that fueled me as an artist, educator, organizer & activist this year. i hope 2019 finds us continuing to  work for collective healing justice, love & beauty! #topnine2018

text:
"when you wake up in the morning, tell yourself: the people i deal with today will be meddling, ungrateful, arrogant, dishonest, jealous and surly. they are like this because they can't tell good from evil. but i have seen the beauty of good, and the ugliness of evil, and have recognized that the wrongdoer has a nature related to my own - not of the same blood and birth, but the same mind, and possessing a share of the divine. and so none of them can hurt me. no one can implicate me in ugliness. nor can i feel angry at my relative, or hate him. we were born to work together like feet, hands and eyes, like the two rows of teeth, upper and lower. to obstruct each other is unnatural. to feel anger at someone, to turn your back on him: these are unnatural.” ~ marcus aurelius

2018 was a strong year. urgent issues surfaced, such as the #metoo movement and #environmental issues. and there's so much to be done. i hope that independently from what this year brings, we glide through it embodying our own #freedom and #kindness. have that personal decision. have a sparkling 2019. 🌟💞

i was 8
when he played games 
with my body 
leaving me
with holes in my skin 
where love
should have grown

i was 16
when they told me
it was my fault

i’m 21
and in every part of me 
he left dirt

i’m planting a seed -flowers don’t choose to be torn off
